title: peanut brittle
directions: Blend well and stir constantly over burner until thermometer reaches 310° or hard crack mark on candy thermometer.
Remove from burner, stirring constantly, and add one heaping teaspoon baking soda and 2 tsp. vanilla.
Stir briskly until thoroughly blended. Pour mixture on to a buttered cookie sheet or buttered foil. Allow to cool until tacky to touch.
Dump and stretch with hands. Allow to cool completely, then crack with back of big spoon.

title: english buttermilk scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking sheet, but don't heat. Sift dry items into a bowl.
Rub in shortening and margarine to get a moist, sand-like texture.
Chill, covered, 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured loaf pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: kay's pistachio squares
directions: Beat together and let set for 2 minutes.
Pour over the cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator for several hours until firm.
Cut and serve.
Also good made with instant lemon.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with Chinese noodles or potato chips and bake at 350° until bubbly hot, and celery and onions are done.
A bouillon cube will help the flavor.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop corned beef, ham and onions, then mix all the ingredients together.
Pat into ball.
Cover it.
Put it in icebox.
It is better if you let it sit overnight.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream the oleo and cheese.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake.

title: spinach salad
directions: Heat the spinach enough to squeeze water out.
Mix jello and water until it starts to thicken. Add the rest of the ingredients. Chill overnight.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: pasta with white beans and tuna fish
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Drain and coat with 1 teaspoon olive oil to keep from sticking; set aside. In large skillet, combine beans, tuna, vegetable stock, 1 tablespoon olive oil, oregano and pasta. Simmer 5 to 7 minutes to allow mixture to thicken. Add salt and pepper. Turn off heat and let sit 20 to 25 minutes. Place in individual serving bowls. Top with Parmesan cheese. Serve warm with tossed salad or serve cold as a salad. Serves 4.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a
medium skillet, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add garlic powder and celery.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp and rice. Cover. Simmer 10 minutes. Add shrimp.
Heat through over low heat.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve over rice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: mustard sauce tuna balls
directions: In a bowl, combine 1 egg and evaporated milk.
Stir in bread crumbs, pimiento, green pepper, Worcestershire, salt, cayenne and tuna.
Chill thoroughly (15 minutes in freezer).
Shape into 8 balls.

title: cole slaw
directions: Place the first 2 ingredients in a large bowl in layers and sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and butter until bubbly.
Pour over eggs; add vanilla and pecans.
Pour in pie shell.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown the ground beef in skillet. Add onion, green pepper, oregano and garlic powder. After beef is browned, add spaghetti sauce and simmer until other ingredients are ready.
In small mixer bowl, combine the Parmesan cheese, eggs and cottage cheese. Mix until blended.
Set aside.
Cook the spaghetti. Drain.
Stir in margarine. Combine cheese mixture
with spaghetti.
Press into pie pans to create pie shells.
Fill pie shells with ground beef mixture. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove pies. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: mountain gravy
directions: In skillet, crumble sausage and cook until browned.
Sprinkle flour over browned sausage, stirring constantly.
When mixture is smooth, slowly add milk.
Stir constantly until creamy and bubbly, about 3 minutes.
Serve hot over homemade biscuits.

title: instant spiced tea mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store in a moisture-proof container.
To serve:
Mix 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons mix with a cup of hot water.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine all ingredients, except bacon in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into lightly greased 2 quart baking dish. Top with bacon.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 4-6.

title: mrs. klatt's freezer cole slaw
directions: Mix salt with cabbage and let sit for one full hour to "draw" water from cabbage.
Then squeeze cabbage; remove/pour off as much water as possible.
Add carrot and green pepper.

title: grits
directions: Cook together water, salt and grits for 5 minutes.
Add butter and garlic powder.
Put cheese on top.
Whip eggs and milk to make 1 cup.
Put in casserole and cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, milk, vanilla and lemon juice on medium speed until well blended.
Pour into crust. Chill 2 hours. Cherry or blueberry pie filling may be added. Pie is ready to serve.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and oregano together.
Spread on a 9-inch pie dish. Mix sauce, pepperoni, onion and green pepper together.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake until bubbly.
Serve with warm breadsticks or hard ones.

title: dutch cucumbers
directions: Mix everything together except cucumbers. Chill. Add cucumbers. Serve as a side dish.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add onions; mix in spices, Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce.
Place beef mixture in large casserole dish.
Add soups and grated cheese.
Place Tater Tots on top to cover entire layer.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until browned.

title: corn flakes krisps
directions: Put sugar and syrup in saucepan and bring it to a boil. Boil it for 1 minute; stir in peanut butter, mix well. Mix in Corn Flakes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flavoring and dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk. Mix well and pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Leave cake in pan.

title: pie dough
directions: In one bowl, sift flour and sugar.
In another bowl, soften shortening; add cold water.
Gradually cut in sifted flour until all flour is mixed in.
Knead until doughy.

title: fiddle creek sandwich
directions: For the Fiddle Creek Sandwich, 4 ounces thin, sliced turkey. Add to the ingredients between the roast beef and ham.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in two 8-inch cake pans.
Layer crumbs, coconut, chocolate bits and butterscotch bits in pan.
Drizzle milk evenly over top.
Cover with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into squares.
Yields 32 cookies.

title: apple cake
directions: Adding in order given, mix and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Pour milk into medium size bowl.
Stir in lemonade. Fold in whipping cream. Do not whip. Can use Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: greek stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Core cabbage and remove leaves one by one.
Steam leaves in covered kettle of salted water until pliable.
Drain and cool. Brown beef and break into small pieces.
Salt and pepper.
Mix raw rice, mint and onion flakes into beef with 1 can tomato sauce (no added water).

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on cooling rack.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Melba thins or crackers.

title: mom's baked bean combo
directions: Fry and cool 4 slices bacon.
Crumble.
Place bacon in crock-pot.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Plug in cooker; heat 1/2 hour. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for about 4 hours.
Makes 2 delicious 2-helping meals.

title: preacher cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine oleo, sugar and milk and cook.
Stir in cocoa, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts or coconut.
Beat well and drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.
Cool.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Remove cores of cabbage.
In a large pot, steam cabbage and remove each leaf as it loosens.
Save hearts of cabbage and chop. Put ground meat in a large bowl.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Mix well; salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato sauce and Ro-Tel tomatoes; mix well.
Add chopped cabbage hearts to meat mixture. Add cooled, cooked rice to meat and cabbage mixture; mix well.
Put one spoon of dressing in each cabbage leaf and roll up.
Place in roaster by layers; salt and pepper each layer.
Put two fingers of water in roaster.
Cook, covered, at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into eight pieces.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Pound with meat tenderizer mallet or edge of a saucer. Place half of meat in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange half of the onion slices over meat.
Repeat layers.
Mix water and catsup and pour over top.

title: creamed corn pudding
directions: Combine milk, eggs and butter and stir until smooth.
Add to corn and mix thoroughly.
Pour into casserole or baking dish and bake in moderate oven at 350° until thickened to desired consistency which is about 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti al dente and cool.
Chop all vegetables very fine.
Combine spaghetti and vegetables.
Sprinkle with Salad Supreme by McCormick.
Pour bottle of dressing over all and toss. Chill and serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry Ranch dressing. Spread over crust.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables over cheese mixture.

title: kristi's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Add vanilla. Mix in flour, sifted with salt and baking powder, kneading toward the last if necessary.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll out a little over 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.
Try dusting your board with a combination of flour and sugar.
It prevents sticking and you won't work in additional flour which hardens and toughens cookies.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Empty soup into small casserole dish; add milk, tuna, peas, cheese and macaroni.
Stir.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: south carolina fresh peach cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Set aside. Combine eggs and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour mixture; beat just until blended .
Dredge peaches and pecans in 1/2 cup flour.
Gently fold into batter.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes in 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.
Cool.
Serve with or without whipped cream.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork.
Form balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for approximately 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar. Beat well with an electric mixer. Stir in buttermilk. Pour into an 8-inch square pan. Freeze mixture until slushy. Beat well with mixer. Return to freezer and freeze until firm.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and parsley in oil until soft. Do not brown. Add all other ingredients. Bring to a boil; turn down to a simmer. Cook until rice is done with the lid on pan.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Combine soup, water, chicken, nuts, celery, onion and 1/2 cup chow mein noodles in a shallow 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved noodles.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: best blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Prepare muffin tin with baking cups.
Stir all dry ingredients together in large bowl.
In a small bowl beat milk, oil and egg using fork or whisk.
Make a well in the center of flour and pour in liquid ingredients all at once.
Stir quickly until dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter will be lumpy.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill cups 2/3 full and bake for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add Cool Whip last and refrigerate.

title: pie pastry or dumplings
directions: Mix salt and plain flour.
Cut in shortening with a fork and add water.
Keep dry and cold. Form ball and roll out thin to desired size on floured board.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix together all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Best if made day ahead.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In large saucepan mix mayo, lemon juice, soup and water; heat. Stir in curry powder.
Put cooked broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan, ungreased, then chopped chicken.
Pour sauce over, then stuffing, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry no-cook jam
directions: Crush strawberries.
In large bowl, stir together strawberries and lemon juice.
Slowly sift in pectin, stirring vigorously.
Set aside 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add corn syrup, stirring well.
Gradually stir in sugar.
When sugar is completely dissolved, ladle into clean 1/2 or 1 pint freezer jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace (no paraffin needed).
Cover with tight lids and put in freezer.
Transfer to refrigerator as needed.

title: microwave cobbler
directions: Combine blackberries and 1 cup sugar.
Microwave for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well the peanut butter, sugar, egg and whole wheat flour.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper; shape into small balls with your hands and flatten each one slightly. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet (12 per sheet).
Unwrap the Hershey's Kisses and press the flat side into the center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool on the pan before removing.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: vegetable gumbo
directions: Fry onions and peppers until tender.
Mix all other ingredients.
Cook/simmer for 25 minutes.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: I put it together in the order given.
Pour batter into greased and floured angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, blend together the first 3 ingredients, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill overnight.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine oleo, milk and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 30 seconds.
Add chocolate chips and beat until spreading consistency.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine margarine, milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly (start timing when mixture starts to "bubble" around the edges of pan).
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute (until marshmallows melt and blend).
Pour into an 8-inch square, buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla. Thoroughly mix the flour, salt, baking powder, soda, coconut, oatmeal, nuts, raisins or dates and orange and lemon rinds.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chili rellenos jose
directions: Carefully rinse seeds from chilies with cold water.
Spread chilies in single layer on paper toweling.
Gently pat with another piece of toweling until dry, then carefully slip a strip of Monterey Jack cheese into each chili.
Beat eggs; gradually add flour, beating until smooth.
Add milk, salt, black pepper and liquid red pepper and beat thoroughly.
Arrange half the stuffed chilies in well-greased 7 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with half the Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Carefully pour egg mixture over all.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven about 45 minutes or until knife inserted in custard comes out clean.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Sift together and blend in dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with greased bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake until a delicate brown and remove immediately from cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: celery dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Process until smooth.
Serve over sliced tomatoes, salad greens or spinach.
Can make 24 hours before and refrigerate. Stir before serving.

title: french-fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and cut into long, fry-sized strips.
Cook in deep fat as you would cook white potato French fries.
Do not add salt.
(Great with ham.)

title: lime pear salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water.
Drain the pears and reserve the juice.
Heat the juice to a boil and add the cream cheese to dissolve.
Set aside to cool.
Mash the pears with a fork.
Cool the gelatin until it begins to gel, then beat for a few minutes.
Add the pear juice and cream cheese mixture.
Add the crushed pears and beat again for a few minutes.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Refrigerate in an oblong glass baking dish.
Top with coconut or red cherries, if desired.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In deep 9-inch round skillet or baking pan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour crushed pineapple on melted brown sugar in bottom of skillet or baking pan and to the sides.
Arrange cherries.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Fill prepared pan 3/4 full and bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until done. While cake is hot, run a knife around edge of cake and invert the cake on a serving plate.

title: cauliflower with a tang
directions: Cook cauliflower until crisp-tender. Drain well and place in serving dish. Combine mayonnaise, mustard and onion while cauliflower is cooking. Spoon over hot cauliflower. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover a few minutes until cheese is melted.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in water.
Cover in saucepan until tender; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Cool.
Combine potatoes with remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Mix gently.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice squash and onions very thin. Put in water and salt. Cover and soak for 3 hrs. Drain off water. Mix vinegar, sugar, and spices. Boil 7 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: crunchy crescent hamwiches
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Blend cream cheese, mayo and mustard until smooth.
Stir in ham, corn, cheese and onion.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Press or roll into 8 x 4-inch rectangle.
Cut into half, crosswise, to form 8 squares.

title: apple cookies
directions: Mix all together, adding the apple, raisins and nuts last. Drop 2 inches apart by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 11 to 14 minutes.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Combine jello, water and frozen strawberries.
Melt margarine, 4 tablespoons sugar and pretzel mix into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese and mix with 1 cup sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cream cheese mixture on top of baked pretzels.
Top with jello mixture.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into large baking dish and top with crushed potato chips or corn flakes with 2 tablespoons of melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apricot salad
directions: Cook until thick, then cool.
Add 1 cup whipped cream to this mixture and spread over firm jello.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter. Stir in wafer crumbs. Pat firmly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.

title: baked clams
directions: Heat oil; cook garlic and onions until brown.
Add breadcrumbs and oregano.
Add 1 can clams with juice.
Season to taste.
Put clams in shells; sprinkle with cheese.
Heat at 350° until light brown or until done.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and season with salt, pepper and onions to taste.
Mix with refried beans.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Stir in softened cream cheese last.
Chill and serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put biscuits, sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag and shake. Pour into angel food cake pan.
Melt margarine and brown sugar together and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli salad supreme
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a blender or food processor until smooth.
Combine broccoli, raisins and onions in a bowl, add cream cheese mixture and toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain. Using large casserole, mix in other ingredients, mixing well.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside. Combine cake mix, apple filling and eggs in a large bowl. Beat with mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes. Combine sugar and cinnamon. Spread half of batter into the baking pan. Sprinkle with half of sugar-cinnamon mixture. Spread rest of batter on top and sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out.

title: texas chili
directions: Place cumin seed in pie pan, bake at 375° for 10 minutes; remove and set aside.
Heat 6-quart cast-iron skillet.
Saute bacon until clear, add diced meat and brown over high heat with onions, garlic and jalapenos.
When meat is brown and onions clear, add remaining ingredients.
Mash tomatoes with your hands. Simmer for 1 hour.
Taste and correct seasoning.
Cooked beans may be added, strictly optional.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, rice, onions, green peppers, pimentos, garlic salt, pepper, soup, mayonnaise and parsley.	Toss lightly. Put in greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until thoroughly heated. Serves 6.

title: "koalslas" holland dutch cole slaw
directions: Heat to boiling the first six ingredients in saucepan.
Add some hot mixture to egg and add back into mixture.
Cook until it thickens.
Take from heat and beat in cream.
Pour (while hot) over finely chopped cabbage.
Chill and serve.

title: sweet and spicy chicken wings
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a bowl.
Toss wings into mixture.
Cover, chill 1 hour.
Drain but save mixture.
Broil wings on cookie sheet, brushing extra mixture on each side.
Broil for 5 minutes on each side.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix salt, sugar, water and vineger and pour over cucumbers. Put remaining ingredients in bottom of the jar.

title: creamy chicken and yellow rice soup
directions: Combine the rice and chicken broth in large saucepan.
Cook according to package directions.
Remove from heat and stir in half and half, milk, chicken, carrots, and black pepper.
Return to heat and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Thin with either chicken broth, milk, or half and half, if needed.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Bake at 325° in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat margarine until melted; remove from oven and stir in seasonings and cheese.
Add cereal, pretzels and peanuts.
Bake for 20 minutes; stir often.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in a 2 1/2-quart bowl over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from water.
Add milk, sugar, peanut butter, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs; let cool about 20 minutes.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls, 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets. Bake in 375° oven (high moderate) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 18 servings.

title: spicy shrimp sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a quart jar.
Shake to mix well. Refrigerate.
Yield:
1 quart.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt butter; add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° until liquid is gone.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
In another bowl, mix together the egg, milk, strawberries and lemon juice.
Combine with dry ingredients and pour into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 425° or 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coffee cake exceptionale
directions: Spread 1/3 of batter in greased tube or Bundt pan and sprinkle with 1/3 of filling (about 6 tablespoons).
Repeat twice. Bake about 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool slightly in pan before removing.

title: one and only occidental hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients very well.
Add milk; cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
That's all.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and cut butter into slices.
Arrange on top.
Cook in a 350° preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: butter beans
directions: Mix altogether.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or microwave for 15 minutes.

title: chris' cucumbers in dill
directions: Pour boiling water over cucumbers.
Let stand 5 minutes. Drain.
Plunge into ice water; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over cucumbers, tossing until well mixed.
Chill 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown the ground beef,
celery and onion and drain well. Add brown sugar, vinegar, ground mustard and catsup.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes or until celery is tender.

title: hawaiian franks
directions: Cook brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar, soy sauce, ginger and syrup from pineapple until thick.
Pour over the pepper strips and onion rings.
Bring hot dogs to a boil.
Drain and add to thickened syrup, etc.
Heat thoroughly.

title: vegetarian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop balls into hot oil until brown. Serve plain or cover with either tomato sauce, sweet and sour sauce or your favorite gravy.

title: scrambled eggs with red peppers and onion
directions: Spray heavy non-stick pan with vegetable spray. Add red pepper and onion and saute over medium heat until tender. Break eggs into medium bowl, whisk, add seasoning blend, add eggs to skillet and reduce heat to low. Stir eggs gently until eggs are set, about 3-4 minutes.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Mix sugar, apple butter and egg at low speed of electric mixer.
Add biscuit mix and flour; mix well.
With spoon, stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs, vanilla, baking soda, salt, baking powder and sour cream.
Gradually add flour until all is used.

title: apple bars
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and cinnamon. Stir together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add nuts and apples; mix.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls into broth.
Boil 18 minutes with cover on the kettle.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook raisins for 10 minutes; drain.
Cook wild rice, drain and cool.
Cut broccoli into pieces.
Add grapes, celery, onions, drained pineapple. Stir in dressing (add a little sugar) and let set overnight.
Add almonds just before serving.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In a small saucepan, heat chili, lite sour cream, water and cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese is thoroughly melted. Remove from heat and serve or add chopped onion, jalapenos and chilies.
Serve as a dip with fat-free tortilla chips.
Great for a party.
Entire recipe makes 6 servings.

title: champagne salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar with mixer until creamy.

title: mocha zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs; add zucchini, oil, vanilla and pudding mix.
Beat until smooth.
Add instant coffee and cake mix.
Mix on low speed until moistened, then on medium speed for 10 minutes.
Turn into a well-greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Top with powdered sugar glaze.

title: party biscuits
directions: Mix well and put in small muffin pan (you can use larger). Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Check for doneness.

title: fluffy orange salad
directions: Beat together cream cheese and cheese spread; drain and cut up peaches, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Beat reserved syrup into cheese; fold in fruits, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Chill 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then add plain flour until mix is stiff enough to roll out (about 2 cups).
Mix well and roll out.
Cut and bake at 350° until brown around edges.

title: pecan macaroons
directions: Mix all together with spoon.
Roll into balls and pat flat but not thin (size of small cookie).
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes, until slightly brown.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: sausage, cheese, egg pie
directions: Brown the sausage in a large skillet.
Drain off fat.
Put cheese in bottom of pie shells, then sausage.
Mix milk and eggs together in a bowl.
Pour mixture over sausage.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: corn soup
directions: Melt margarine; saute onions.
Add salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add flour; stir.
Put back on heat; add milk, corn and bouillon cubes.
Stir until thick.
Add Worcestershire and take off heat.
Do not at any time let milk boil.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Layer bottom of greased casserole dish with the pieces of chicken.
Next, layer the broccoli spears on top of the chicken. Then mix all the other ingredients together and pour over top of the chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar; add nuts, oil, eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, and salt. Add flour mixture to apple mixture and mix until well blended. Bake in greased 9x13 inch pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: uncle gary's fish soup
directions: In a stock pot, cook the bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon. Add onion, pepper, celery and garlic.
Stir over medium heat until tender, about 7 minutes.
Add back crumbled bacon and all other ingredients except fish.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add fish and stir gently to mix, then simmer until fish flakes easily, about 8 minutes.

title: chicken alberghetti
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Dip in egg and roll in crumbs.
Saute in butter until browned.
Dilute spaghetti sauce with cream.
Keep out 2 tablespoons of mixture.
Pour sauce in bottom of covered casserole dish.
Add chicken.
Top each piece of chicken with one slice Mozzarella cheese and one slice Swiss.
Add reserved sauce.
Sprinkle with butter and Parmesan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and salt in saucepan.
Cook to rolling boil and continue cooking for one minute.
Remove from heat, add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix, drop on wax paper.

title: almond drops
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper-covered baking sheet.
Chill until set, about 4 hours. Store in fridge.
Yields about 7 dozen.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and melt.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Beat with mixer.
Add grated cheese, spinach, onion and melted butter from pan.
Spoon into baking dish and level off.
Sprinkle lightly with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.
Freezes well.
Reheats well.

title: tamala corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except green chilies and Cheddar cheese. Put half of the mixture in square baking dish.
Top with chili mix, chilies and grated cheese.
Add remaining corn mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes in oven at 375°.

title: butterscotch spectacular
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix together flour, butter and pecans.
Pat in thin layer in 3-quart pan or glass dish.
Bake in 350° oven 20 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: clam chowder
directions: Chop and fry bacon and onions together.
Dice potatoes.
Put in saucepan with 1/2 of bacon drippings, juice of clams and 1 cup of milk.
Cook until tender.
Add bacon, onion, soup, 1 cup milk and clams.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until bubbly.

title: baklava
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small saucepan and cook syrup until sugar dissolves; cool.

title: date nut pumpkin bread
directions: Measure all dry ingredients into a sifter.
Set aside.
Beat eggs in a large bowl; add sugar and pumpkin.
Stir well.
Add all dry ingredients with small amounts of oil and water.
Mix well. Add dates and nuts.

title: date cake
directions: Mix all but last three ingredients together and place in greased cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, sugar and nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour.
Mix well with strawberries and rhubarb.
Place in pie crust and dot with butter.
Put on top crust sealing edges well.
Brush top crust with cold water and sprinkle on 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Cut steam vents.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 40 to 50 minutes or until rhubarb is tender and crust is brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon together.
Place in a baking dish.
Make topping of flour, brown sugar, pecans and margarine. Spoon over apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and chill several hours.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Stir gently.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour one half of mixture in long baking dish.
Chill until congealed.
Spread sour cream over top.
Spoon remaining gelatin mixture over sour cream.
Add nuts. Chill until firm.

title: spiced pot roast in crock-pot
directions: Put roast in crock-pot.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water. Mix all remaining ingredients.
Pour over roast.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Combine salt, pepper, water, sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Boil for several minutes.
Cool and pour over the vegetables.
Chill for 24 hours and serve.

title: spiced cranberries
directions: Cook cranberries with sugar and water 8 to 10 minutes.
Add orange and spices.
Cook 1 minute.
This will keep 2 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.
Freezes well.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix the ingredients and freeze.
When ready to serve, break frozen mix with a fork and gradually add 4 large bottles of ginger ale.
Makes 50 cups.

title: spicy appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together except paprika.
Spread on Wheat Thins; sprinkle paprika on top and broil for 3 to 4 minutes.
These are wonderful, believe it or not.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix Eagle brand and cream cheese.
Fold in pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Freeze.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening.
Combine egg and milk and add to flour mixture all at once.
Stir until dough follows fork around bowl; turn out on floured surface and knead 20 strokes.
Roll 3/4-inch thick and cut.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 14 minutes.
May be refrigerated for 1 to 3 hours before baking. Makes 24 small biscuits.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to boil.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Stir in chocolate, cream, nuts and vanilla.

title: governor's meat loaf
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper slightly. Add to beef with remaining ingredients. Place in 2 small or 1 large loaf pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread mixture on a small serving plate or put in small individual bowls.
Top with nuts.
Serve with apple wedges. Yield:
6 servings.

title: christmas morning casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in greased, glass 2-quart casserole.
Fry bacon until well done.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle on bread cubes.
Beat together eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over bread and bacon.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Wrap tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in cold oven set to 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine rice, celery, salt and soup in casserole dish.
Add 2 cups cold water and stir in milk powder.
Arrange chicken on rice. Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix strawberry jello with 3/4 cup boiling water; stir until dissolved, then add 1/2 cup cold water.
Poke holes in warm cake.
Pour jello into holes and refrigerate while mixing together pudding, Dream Whip and 1 1/2 cups of cold milk.
Frost cake and refrigerate again.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 10-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 minutes.
This will taste like a pecan pie.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook
macaroni	just tender.
Mix other ingredients and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut chocolate dessert
directions: Crust:
cut butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in 2/3 cup nuts.
Press mixture in a 13 x 9 inch pan and bake for 20 minutes.

title: mckinnon family cheesecake for the holidays
directions: Mix eggs, cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla, milk, flour and sugar into large bowl with blender.
Grease a 9-inch or 11-inch spring-form pan.
Turn oven on to 350°.
Mix melted butter with chopped graham crackers and line the pan for the crust of the cheesecake.
Pour the mixture into the spring-form pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until cake turns golden brown.
Cake may crack in the middle of the top.
"That's a good sign."

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix together with butter and cheese. Spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add milk until you can see it under the top layer of macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Gently stir mixture.
Bake for an additional 30 to 40 minutes.

title: micro tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble and microwave beef on High for 5 minutes. Top with onion, salt, pepper and Tater Tots. Combine 2 soups and pour over beef mixture.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: play dough
directions: Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup of cold water.
Boil salt and 1/2 cup of water.
Mix in starch.
Work in 1 teaspoon salad oil.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Save 1/2 cup boiled water from vegetables (to keep moist).

title: crusty cheese rings
directions: Combine flour and butter in mixing bowl.
Cut butter into flour until mixture is slightly smaller than peas.
Mix in cream and vinegar with fork.
Stir in cheese evenly.
Form dough into ball.
Roll out on lightly floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into rings using a doughnut cutter.
Repeat using all dough. Place rings and holes on ungreased baking sheet about 1 inch apart.
Chill 30 minutes.
Brush tops with egg white.
Sprinkle additional cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix well.
Add Cool Whip last.
Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: 'skins
directions: Cut potato in 4 wedges.
Scrape potato, leaving about 1/2-inch of potato on skins.
French fry in hot fat until golden brown. Sprinkle with cheese and finely chopped bacon.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Beat by hand.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together in separate bowl.
Add mixture and beat by hand.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When done, spread marshmallows evenly on cake.
Put back in oven until they melt. Let cool.
Add icing.

title: chili sauce
directions: Wash tomatoes, scald, peel and quarter.
Put on stove to boil until cooked, about 15 to 20 minutes, then drain off 2 quarts of clear tomato juice.
Cut celery into small pieces.
Chop green pepper, onion and red pepper through food chopper or blender. Combine all vegetables with tomato, sugar, salt and vinegar. (Spices should be tied in cheesecloth).
Boil 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.
Remove spice bag.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal securely.

title: spinach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water.
Add mayo and lemon juice.
Let set until slightly firm, then add all the rest.

title: garden chopped salad
directions: Tear romaine lettuce into bit size pieces, add bell pepper, carrots, cucumber, tomatoes and scallions.
Cut avocado into 1/4 inch dices, place in a small bowl and toss with lime juice to coat well.
Combine with all the ingredients and toss with ranch dressing.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: aunt eva's chicken delight
directions: Saute chicken breasts to a golden color, then saute onion, cut in small pieces.
Parboil the broccoli.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Microwave 4 ounces corn on High for 4 1/2 minutes.
Put in pan first 3 ingredients.
Add popped corn.
Heat on medium until all sugar is dissolved, while stirring.
Cool to touch and form into 12 balls.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, crackers, 1 large onion (chopped), 1 egg, 1 can tomato sauce and salt to taste.
Mix with hands.
Place in oblong pan.
Makes large size. Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease and flour a large skillet.
Mix all together except cheese.
Pour half of batter in skillet, then sprinkle cheese over top.
Pour rest of batter in.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cappuccino biscotti
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine coffee granules and hot water in a small bowl.
Stir in vanilla and next 2 ingredients and add to flour mixture, stirring until well blended.

title: tuna corn chowder
directions: Drain tuna.
Saute onion and celery in butter or margarine. Add 1 1/2 cups water to pan and bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; cover and cook until tender.
Add tuna, corn, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lo-cal vegetable soup
directions: Using a food processor, slice vegetables. Transfer to a 3 or 4-quart saucepan. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a full boil; cover, then simmer 1 hour.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.
Contains 65 calories each.

title: chunk pickles
directions: Cut pickles up small (1/2-inch).
Make brine of water and salt. Let stand in brine overnight.
Drain, then take 1 cup vinegar and 6 quarts water; add pickles.
Steam but don't boil until they lose their dark green color.
Drain and put pickles in jars and cover with 2 1/2 cups vinegar, 2 1/2 cups water, 4 3/4 cups sugar and 1/2 teaspoon celery seed.
Boil for 5 minutes and pour over pickles. Put a little dill and 3 to 4 slices garlic in first; seal jars.

title: texas country bean soup mix
directions: Combine all of the beans.
Mix well.
Yield: 20 cups.
Divide into 10 portions (2 cups each).
This is wonderful included in a Christmas basket along with a recipe for Ten Bean Soup.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Slice hot dogs down the middle long ways. Don't go all the way through.
Put cheese in the sliced hot dog. Wrap bacon around the hot dog. Broil in oven for 5 minutes. Turn over and broil 5 more minutes.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well and pour over crackers. Stir until all is absorbed.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix chicken and mushroom soups, onion, mushrooms, milk and spices.
Mix in rice.
Cover bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan with the rice mixture.
Place chicken on top of the rice. Sprinkle the onion soup mix on the chicken.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Brown pie shells. Melt butter in microwave. Grate apples. Mix with butter. Add cinnamon and sugar to taste. Bake at 375° until apples are done.

title: zesty cucumber treats
directions: Mix cheese, dressing mix, mayonnaise and hot sauce together. Spread on rye bread slices.
Top with 1/4-inch slice cucumber. Sprinkle paprika over each for color and taste.
Cheese mixture can be stored in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: spaghetti sauce for canning
directions: Cook together in a large kettle for 2 1/2 hours.
Put through a food mill.

title: chunk or 7 day pickles
directions: Wash pickles and put in vessel, make enough salt water to cover.
Let stand 3 days.
The fourth day, put clear water and then change water for 3 days, then wash good and cut in desired shapes.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Combine margarine, milk, and sugar in a large skillet and bring to a boil, stirring, over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring constantly, for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Add cracker crumbs and nuts, blending well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool completely.
Store in a covered container. Yield: about 4 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage.
Trim crusts from bread.
Arrange in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine milk, eggs, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Beat well.
Drain sausage.
Mix with mustard. Spread over bread slices.
Add cheese. Pour egg mixture over bread, sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all (except cheese and chips).
Put in oblong dish.
Put cheese and chips over mixture.
In preheated oven, bake 15 to 20 minutes. Be watchful, as it burns easily.

title: chocolate snow-top cookies
directions: In bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Over hot (not boiling) water, melt the chocolate chips, stirring until smooth.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Drain sweet potatoes.
Add cinnamon, salt and sugars.
Mix with fork.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, vanilla and honey by hand.
Slowly pour egg mixture into sweet potato mixture.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: crab and cheese muffins
directions: Blend all ingredients (except muffins) in pan over low heat. Spread thickly over muffins.
Broil for 2 to 3 minutes, until golden brown.
Cut into wedges.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt Cheddar cheese (Velveeta).
Mix together.
Make into inch balls.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.
(Put far enough apart so won't touch.)
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: pauline's cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over 1 cup quick cook oatmeal and 1 stick butter or oleo; let stand 2 minutes.
Add all the ingredients (except topping).
Beat smooth.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix and heat until creamy in microwave.
Cut crisp apples and dip.

title: tasty spuds
directions: Slice potatoes in quarter pieces.
Pat dry with paper towel. Roll in melted butter.
Sprinkle each with salad dressing mix, cheese and flour.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Heat water, cocoa and oil to boil.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, sugar and salt.
Combine first ingredients.
Mix sour milk with soda, vanilla and eggs.
Mix with previous batter.
Pour into 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Frost.

title: yogurt-fruit surprise
directions: Put 2 to 3 tablespoons of low-fat yogurt in a bowl.
Add 4 teaspoons orange juice and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add fresh fruit to mixture.
Serves one.

title: frozen peach pie filling
directions: For fried pies or cobblers, cook until thick.
Freeze.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or mix together in crock-pot.
Cook for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll them up into a log shape and chill until ready to serve.
Slice logs into 1-inch pieces.
Chilling
for an hour or more improves flavor. Serve with salsa or guacamole.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cheese, onion and pepper in a medium-size bowl.
Add tomato sauce and cooking oil; then mix with spoon until all cheese mixture has been moistened.
Slice off tops of rolls; scoop out centers.
Spoon filling into rolls; replace tops of rolls and bake, uncovered, on a cookie sheet for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Put sour cream in bowl and add dry jello.
Stir until sugar granules are completely dissolved.
Fold in Cool Whip and fruit.

title: my favorite gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together the butter, brown sugar, egg and molasses; set aside.
Sift the dry ingredients.
Combine the ingredients and stir until smooth.
Put dots of 1/8 teaspoon of dough 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet and bake 5 to 6 minutes. Cool on rack.
Cookies snap off if you twist the sheet slightly.

title: dessert burgers
directions: Alternately beat flour mixture and 1 cup milk into creamed mixture.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased baking sheet to make 24 rounds.
Bake at 425° for 6 minutes.

title: texas and mississippi caviar
directions: Shake dressing, sugar, green pepper, vinegar, salt, black pepper.
Combine peas and other ingredients.
Toss pea mixture with dressing mixture, adjust seasonings.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: marinated veggies
directions: Drain cans of vegetables.
Combine vinegar, oil and sugar. Bring to a boil.
Pour over veggies.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: easter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup lukewarm milk with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks and a little flour.
(I use my mixer as long as I can.)
Add rest of ingredients, including yeast and enough lukewarm milk to make a soft dough.
Work until it does not stick to hands or bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk (does not rise a lot).
Take pieces and make long skinny rolls, then braid them. (In twos or threes.)

title: dirty pudding
directions: Crush cookies with food processor.
Put half on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk and softened cream cheese. Blend in Cool Whip.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Combine margarine, flour, sugar, milk and vanilla; mix well. Then mix sugar, brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Add 1 3/4 cups hot water on top and bake at 375° until done.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients. Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Fold in raisins and pecans.
Spoon into a 12-cup Bundt pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Contains 4.5 grams fat, 54.8 grams carbohydrates and
41 mg.
cholesterol.

title: double-dutch fudge cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat Crisco, then add moist ingredients, one by one.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to moist ones and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes (don't overbake).
Once out of oven, let cool for several minutes before removing from sheet and placing onto wired rack.
Enjoy!

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble up bread good.
Pour both kinds of milk over bread. Take hands or potato masher and mash.
Beat egg good and pour into bread mixture.
Put sugar, vanilla and butter on top.
Put nutmeg in.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: chicken cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook broccoli in 6 cups of water until tender.
Add all other ingredients and cook until cheese melts.

title: soda biscuits
directions: Cut in shortening with dry mixture.
Add milk with egg.
Make mixture about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut biscuits with biscuit cutter and put biscuits on a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix these ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Roll in pecans, if desired.

title: pink salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and pineapple in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Cool.
Fold in Dream Whip, cottage cheese and pecans.
Place in 1-quart mold and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or until firm.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies to make crumbs.
Melt margarine and mix with crumbs.
Press crumbs into 13 x 9-inch dish, reserving 1/2 cup crumbs for topping.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat oil and egg.
Add oats and orange juice.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in berries.
Bake 400° 10 -12 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soups, broth, chilies and spices.
Grease pan.
Put chips, chicken, sauce and cheese, layering until cheese is on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: low-fat spinach dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Hollow out bread and tear into pieces.
Fill bread with dip.
Serve with torn up bread pieces and fresh veggies.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Prepare each jello package separately using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each. Pour each into an 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes. Dissolve remaining package of orange jello and sugar in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pineapple juice and chill until slightly thickened.
Blend whipped topping into gelatin. Fold in gelatin cubes and pour into 9-cup tube pan.
Chill overnight or until firm.
Unmold and garnish with whipped topping.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: crusty chicken breasts
directions: Mix mayonnaise, melted margarine and mustard until smooth. Dip chicken breasts into this mixture and then roll into stuffing mix.
Place in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes until brown. The herb stuffing takes care of the flavor.
I use fat free mayonnaise and fat free margarine.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine. Add ground beef and brown. Drain excess grease. Add cream of chicken soup and mushrooms, salt and pepper. Cook approximately 5 minutes.
Just before serving, add sour cream and heat thoroughly. I add poppy seed when I add the soup and mushrooms. Serve with rice or noodles. Serves approximately 6.

title: old fashioned caramel icing
directions: Mix all ingredients except the additional 1/2 cup sugar in a large saucepan.
Once this gets hot, put the additional 1/2 cup sugar into skillet and melt until brown on medium-low heat, then pour into the saucepan with the other ingredients.
Cook until a soft ball can be formed.
Remove from heat and stir until creamy and thickened.
Spread over any plain cake.

title: dreamy creamy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken; pat dry with paper towel. Place the breasts in large shallow casserole.
Combine soup, mushrooms with liquid and sour cream in small bowl; mix well with wooden spoon.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake chicken, uncovered, for 1 1/4 hours, until tender.
Serve with vegetables of your choice for a mouth watering meal.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well; drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Slice apples into buttered pie plate.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. In bowl, combine butter, flour, sugar, salt, egg and nuts.
Mix well, just enough to moisten.
Dough will be thick.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, beating until well blended. Fold topping into mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze until firm before serving.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine the first 10 ingredients in order, stirring after each addition.
Boil until thick.
Cool before adding the Miracle Whip salad dressing.

title: apple pudding
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place them in casserole or buttered dish.
Add water and cinnamon.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and the butter until mixture falls in small pieces.
Spread mixture over the apples.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with cream.

title: strawberry bread
directions: 1. Sift dry ingredients in a large bowl. 2. Mix remaining ingredients except for nuts and strawberries. 3. Add to dry ingredients and fold in strawberries and nuts. 4. Bake in 9 x 5 loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: baked turkey with dressing
directions: Thaw turkey.
Remove
giblets
and
neck
from
cavity. Wash turkey and
drain
well.
Rub
cavity
with
salt.
Stuff cavity loosely with your choice of dressing.
Place in roasting pan and baste turkey with melted butter.
Pour 1 cup water in bottom
of roasting pan.
Make a foil boat around sides of turkey to
place remaining dressing in to keep dressing out of the water.
Cover turkey
with foil, then place lid on.
Bake in oven
at
for approximately 4 1/2 to 5 hours or until turkey
is
tender. Approximately 30 minutes before turkey is done, remove lid.
Foil cover and brown turkey.
Remove turkey from oven
and
let
sit for
approximately
15 to 20 minutes before slicing.

title: cabbage and rice casserole
directions: In pan, put cabbage (chopped), water, salt and margarine. Cook to tender-crisp, then add rice.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook second set of ingredients just to melt cheese. Pour cabbage mixture in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Cover with cheese sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain well.
Combine all ingredients and simmer, covered, for 2 to 4 hours.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Heat chili sauce and jelly over low heat, stirring constantly until jelly is melted.

title: easy pear cobbler
directions: Chop
fruit
and use juice.
Layer fruit with juice with cake mix
in
large casserole.
Put a layer of cake mix on top. Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in the butter until soft.
Add the beef consomme and water to the onion.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and garlic powder.
Simmer on low for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake for 10 minutes at 440°, then about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: robert e. lee's gingersnaps
directions: With mixer, beat together butter, molasses, sugar and eggs. Add 4 cups flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves, all at once. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Work in additional flour (if necessary). Shape into small balls (1-inch diameter) and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Combine meat, onions and one cup of cheese; mix.
Some cook this but I don't.
In a heavy skillet or your deep fryer, heat oil.
Using tongs, dip tortillas one at a time in hot oil for 10 seconds or just until limp.
Drain on paper towels.
Spoon a 1/4 cup meat mixture on tortilla; roll up and place seam down in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Heat sauces and pour over top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes; add cheese on top the last 15 minutes of cooking time.

title: bubble solution
directions: Mix all ingredients and use pipe cleaners or six pack rings to make your own wands.

title: spiced smoked goose
directions: You will need hickory wood chips and smoker.

title: hawaiian drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream the shortening, sugar and extracts thoroughly. Beat in egg until mixture is fluffy. Blend in pineapple and dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet 3-inches apart.
Sprinkle with coconut. Bake in a 325° oven about 20 minutes. Cookies are better stored for 24 hours.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen 2 1/2-inch diameter cookies.

title: banana pudding
directions: Pour cold milk into large mixing bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
Add condensed milk; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put layer of pudding, then layers of bananas and wafers until you use up all pudding.
Chill for 3 hours.
Makes large bowl full.

title: chewy batter squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, margarine and 1 egg. Pat mixture into an 11 x 14-inch pan.
Combine the cream cheese, 3 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Beat with mixer.
Pour cream cheese mixture over cake mixture.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cut into small squares.
Enjoy.

title: cast and fire's enchiladas
directions: In a
skillet, heat oil and dip each tortilla in quickly. Place each on a paper towel to drain.
This is to make it soft and pliable.
When
done,
remove
oil
and
put in 1 can enchilada sauce
and
heat.
Dip
a
tortilla in the sauce and place on a plate.
Add
some
cheese
and
onion and roll up. Place in a pan or Dutch oven.
Repeat until Dutch oven is full or pan is
full. Mix
the chili with no beans and the rest of the enchilada
sauce together.
Pour over enchiladas (you may want to heat
the
chili and
sauce to mix).
Place in a 300° oven and heat 30 to 40 minutes.

title: glendith's butter pie
directions: Cream this together, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla and little over 1 cup milk.
Pour into crust and bake.

title: dump cake
directions: Place fruit cocktail in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread dry cake mix over fruit (don't mix together).
Dot with butter. Bake until golden brown in 350° preheated oven.
Serve hot with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream

title: date nut pinwheels
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water.
Cook about 3 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon peel and chopped walnuts. Divide dough in half and roll each half into an 8 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread with half of date mixture.
Roll into jelly type roll and refrigerate for 8 hours. Slice about 1/2-inch thick and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hummus dip
directions: In a food processor, combine garbanzo beans, tahini paste, lemon juice and yogurt.
Blend until smooth.
Add green onion, cumino, garlic and salt.
Blend.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Spread over a plate.
Drizzle olive oil over the top.
Garnish with mint.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add 7-Up; add pineapple which has been drained (save liquid). Pour mixture into baking dish. Spread marshmallows on top and let chill until set.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Cook with small onion, stalk of celery and celery leaves.
Add salt.
Cook until tender (about 2 hours for hen).
Combine in saucepan 3/4 cup of stock (substitute 1/2 cup stock, 1/2 cup white wine), mushroom soup, juice from can of mushrooms, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until smooth. Add mushrooms.
Cook spaghetti in chicken stock, adding bouillon cube if not enough stock.
Put 1/2 of the spaghetti in casserole dish, then 1/2 chicken, then 1/2 sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 8.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar together.
Add slightly beaten egg, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add chopped apples.
Pour mixture into a pastry-lined 9 inch pie plate.
Bake in a hot oven 425° 15 minutes; then reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and add crumb topping.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Beat eggs.
Add corn, 1/2 of muffin mix and onion mixture.
Put in greased casserole.
Spread with sour cream.
Sprinkle with cheese and dry muffin mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scrumptious busy day casserole
directions: Do not brown the meat.
Place all ingredients in a roaster or large casserole dish in the order listed of ingredients.
No need to mix.
Place in the oven, uncovered.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours or until done.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: beer-batter fried walleye
directions: Beat egg yolks and beer together.
Gently stir flour and salt until blended.
Mix in margarine and allow to stand at room temperature 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad 2
directions: Cook noodles, drain and set aside.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss in noodles.
Chill in the refrigerator for about an hour before serving.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Sift flour and salt into large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Add eggs, oil and water.
Work liquids into flour with fingers to make a stiff dough. Turn dough onto a large board.
Do not add flour.
Knead dough 15 times or until soft and smooth. Wrap in Saran Wrap and let sit at room temperature 1 hour.

title: skillet stew
directions: Cook beef in skillet; add onion and spices.
In large pot, cook tomatoes, beans, carrots, rice and water until rice is tender; add meat mixture to rice mixture, adding water if needed. When stew has reached desired consistency, serve.
With less water, stew can be served as a casserole.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and pineapple.
Place in buttered casserole dish and top with crushed crackers mixed with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole no. 2
directions: Mix squash,
soup,
onion and sour cream.
Put layer of stuffing mix in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Add squash mixture and
top
with
layer of stuffing mix.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients. Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into pieces and cook.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients saving 1/2 of cheese to sprinkle on top.
Place in a 2-quart casserole and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: creole oyster pie
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet. Stir next 6 ingredients into drippings. Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add flour, salt and red pepper, stirring well. Stir in crumbled bacon, oysters, parsley, lemon juice and water. Spoon mixture into lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Combine biscuit mix and milk. Roll dough out on lightly floured surface to fit baking pan.
Place pastry over oyster mix and cut slits in pastry.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until crust is golden.

title: toasted spice cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; slowly add brown sugar.
Sprinkle on top and finish baking:

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together and let come to a boil, just for a minute or two.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and mix.
Add pumpkin, milk, salt and spices to eggs.
Cook over hot water until thick, stirring constantly about 10 minutes.
Add gelatin to hot pumpkin mixture and stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Let cool.

title: white trash
directions: Mix all ingredients EXCEPT the white chocolate chips in a large bowl. Melt the white chocolate chips in a bowl in the microwave for 3 minutes on High power. Stir. Continue for an additional minute if necessary. Pour over mixture in the large bowl. Mix well. Spread onto waxed paper. When hard, break into pieces.

title: billye's t-cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add egg and flour, a little at a time, baking powder, nutmeg and vanilla; more flour may be needed to make a stiffer batter.
(Roll out on flour sprinkled board and cut in shapes; may use a water glass to cut shapes.)
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: huevos rancheros
directions: In a
skillet, dip tortillas in hot oil quickly.
Place on paper towels.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon of oil.
Heat oil and saute
onion
and
garlic.
Add
tomato sauce, oregano and chili powder;
simmer
about 5 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Crack the eggs in
a
bowl
and put them in the sauce.
Cover with a lid
or foil and simmer until the eggs are poached.
Don't let the
sauce
lose to
much
moisture.
Place
one
egg on each tortilla and spoon sauce over each; top with grated cheese.

title: canned beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil gently for 40 minutes. Pack in hot jars with liquid covering beans. Seal.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Boil brown sugar
and
cream
together until it makes a soft ball in cold water.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Boil slowly for 3 minutes
in
a
steady boil.
Remove from stove and beat until firm enough to be dropped by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: grape-nut pudding for 12
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Cover bottom of a 4-quart baking dish with Grape-Nuts.
Pour mixture over Grape-Nuts.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Let set.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer in a large pot for 10 minutes. Makes 3 quarts.

title: easiest popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar and Karo until mixture boils.
Butter hands; pour over popped corn that has been put into a large, buttered bowl. Make balls.

title: apricot dessert
directions: Heat sugar and nectar.
Beat yolks and beat in sugar and nectar.
Mix slowly and bring to a boil.
Add jello and let cool. Fold in whipped milk and chill.

title: almost potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and add dressing, toss well, serve chilled.

title: "robbie's fried chicken"
directions: You flour the chicken, put it in the skillet with some hot grease and cook it until it taste good.
It's even better cold the next day.

title: quick-to-fix taco salad
directions: In a large skillet, cook the turkey or pork sausage until browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in enchilada sauce, drained chili peppers and drained mushrooms.
Bring sausage mixture to boiling. Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 2 minutes.

title: mama's eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in small pieces.
Parboil in salted water until it begins to clear.
Lightly saute onion and celery in oil.
Drain eggplant and add to skillet.
Add tomatoes; season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire and stir in egg.
Pour into casserole, dot with margarine and cover with crushed corn flakes. Bake uncovered 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato cheese bake
directions: Saute onion in 1 stick of butter.
Add to sour cream and chicken soup.
Stir thoroughly.
Add hash browns and cheese.
Pour mixture into an 11 x 13-inch glass baking dish (spray with Pam first).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly and golden brown on top.
This dish is quick and easy and great for company.

title: cream cheese braids
directions: Combine scalded sour cream, sugar, butter and salt; mix well. Let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; stir in sour cream mixture, then eggs.
Gradually stir in flour (dough will be soft).
Cover tightly and chill overnight.

title: golden glow sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender; drain and let cool just enough to handle, then peel.
Mash potatoes and combine with 2 1/2 cups marshmallows, butter, milk, brown sugar, nutmeg, salt and cinnamon.
Whip until fluffy.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine shortening, salt and sugar in bowl.
Add hot water. Cool to lukewarm.
In cold water, dissolve yeast cakes and add to mixture.
Add eggs (well beaten), then 3 cups flour and mix well. Mix remaining flour.
Stir thoroughly, but do not knead.
Cover and put in refrigerator until ready to use.
When you remove from refrigerator to use, should be double in bulk.
Mash down with a little flour.
Make out rolls.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Brush tops with butter.
Dough will keep, covered, several days in refrigerator.

title: steak marinade provencale
directions: Combine all ingredients; use to marinate any steak for about an hour.
Use marinade to baste beef while cooking.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers, confectioners sugar, nuts, margarine and juice.
Form into balls.
May be rolled in coconut or confectioners sugar immediately after making balls.
Store in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion; drain.
In blender combine tomatoes, tomato paste and water until smooth.
Add seasonings. Blend until mixed.
Pour over browned meat.
Add mushrooms. Simmer uncovered 3/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break angel food cake up in pieces in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Boil 2 cups of water and stir in jello.
Pour over strawberries and stir.
Pour all over the cake.
Make pudding according to directions.
Put over the strawberry mixture, then put Cool Whip over the pudding.
Garnish with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: dessert bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients by hand until crumbly. Put into a 9 x 13 greased pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, oil and eggs.
Add vanilla. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour into greased tube pan or two loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325 degrees.
Let cool and turn onto plate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar, syrup and salt in water. Add peanuts and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until peanuts are parched done. Add butter and vanilla. Stir in soda and pour in large greased cookie sheet.
As mixture begins to harden around edges, begin to pull thin.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients listed and put in graham cracker crust and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, flour and vanilla; fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Separate biscuits and roll to an oblong shape.
Lay a slice of cheese on each oblong biscuit.
Roll biscuit and cheese around sausage, letting sausage tips show at each end.
Place sealed edge down on an ungreased pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve.
Good for lunches or after school snacks.

title: shrimp alfredo
directions: Boil shrimp.
Peel; set aside.
Cook fettucine.
Drain.
Mix cheese, butter, whipping cream, parsley and pepper.
Toss until noodles are evenly coated.
Add shrimp.
Serve hot.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal and flour, mixing well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry mixture, stirring until smooth.
Pour the batter into well-greased cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Invert on a plate.
Serves 8.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, drain grease.
Add cream cheese, soup, catsup to ground beef.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350 degrees.
Top with biscuits and bake until brown.

title: apple bean bake
directions: In skillet, melt margarine.
Add cubed apples and cook until tender.
Add sugars.
Stir and cook until melted.
Stir in cinnamon, catsup and molasses.
Add beans.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: best ever baking powder biscuits
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder in bowl; add shortening and cut in with pastry blender.
Add milk, a little at a time, until soft but not sticky dough is formed.
Roll out 3/4-inch thick on floured board.
Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: stuffed meat roll
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients; mix well.
On foil or wax paper, pat meat to about a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on top.
Sprinkle cheese, onion and mushrooms on top of ham. Carefully roll up meat, using foil to lift.
Seal edges and ends. Place roll, seam down, in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes, or until done.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve hot.

title: palace city corn
directions: Stir ingredients together in baking dish. Stir occasionally while baking for 1 hour at 350° or cook in crock-pot on low for 3 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Place cranberries in saucepan with enough water to just come even with berries.
Boil until berries fall to pieces.
Strain all juice and then discard pulp (should have about 5 cups of juice).
Dissolve jello and sugar in the 3 cups boiling water. Add strained juice to jello.
Add undiluted orange juice and pecans.
Mix well and place in mold.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: mary jo's (sparks) apple crisp
directions: Prepare apples as
you
would
for pie.
Put in pan and cover with cinnamon/sugar
and
pats
of
butter.
Cover
with enough water to
start
apples.
Mix
other
ingredients
with pastry blender until
crumbly.
Put mixture over apples covering apples completely.
Cover
pan with aluminum foil and bake for 20 minutes at 350°,
then take off foil and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
When
done,
remove from oven and drizzle melted butter over apple crisp.

title: maid rites
directions: Cook hamburger, water, onion and catsup for 15-20 minutes. Add mustard, salt, and pepper. Simmer a little longer and fill buns for serving.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and milk. Add 2 cups flour, salt, baking powder, vanilla and cinnamon. Beat until smooth. Add remaining flour until mixture is thick to proper consistency to go through a funnel. Pour 1/2 cup of batter through a funnel into heated oil (375°). Fry on both sides. Remove from oil and do the remainder of batter using 1/2 cup or more batter as you wish to make desired size of cakes.

title: super quick sticky rolls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup.
Blend well.
Spread evenly in bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch round pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Remove dough from can.
Separate into 8 coils (do not unroll breadsticks).

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk. Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast, sugar, water and egg to milk. Beat with rotary beater until blended. Add 3 1/2 cups flour, fat and salt to yeast mixture. Stir until blended. Add remaining flour, stirring until blended. Place in greased bowl. Grease top. Cover and store in refrigerator. Remove from refrigerator. Shape into rolls. Brush top with fat. Let double in size. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. May use for cinnamon rolls.

title: spanish stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine cilantro, pepper and tarragon in small bowl; mix. Brown pork in skillet, season with 1/2 of seasoning mix.
Break up pork as it cooks, well done.
Remove and drain well.
Repeat for beef.
Combine both meats in large mixing bowl and crumble well. Add onion and blend well.
Add sour cream and mustard and blend well.
Add cheese.
Wash mushrooms.
Remove stem to create bowl. Using teaspoon, fill each, taking care not to break.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: strawberry onion salad
directions: In a large bowl toss the romaines lettuce, strawberries and onion.
