Combine rest of ingredients in a small jar, mix well. Serve immediately.

title: stuff peppers
directions: Cook peppers in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
Cook and stir beef and onions until tender; drain off fat.
Stir in garlic salt, cooked rice and 1 cup tomato sauce; heat through.
Stuff each pepper, place in baking dish.
Pour cup of tomato sauce over and cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, remove lid and bake for 15 minutes uncovered.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple completely; fold in Cool Whip.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Enjoy!!!

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Slice cabbage thin; cook 5 minutes and drain. Put milk, soup and mayonnaise in a saucepan and heat.
Combine crumbs and margarine in a bowl.
Use 1/2 of crumb mixture in bottom of casserole.
Add cabbage and sauce.
Then add remaining crumb mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly and hot.

title: beet and potato salad(russia)
directions: Mix the diced vegetables and season to taste with salt, pepper and fresh dill. Add just enough oil to moisten the vegetables.

title: waikiki meat balls
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, crumbs, onion, eggs, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown and cook meat balls.
Remove meat balls.
Keep warm.
Pour fat from skillet.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients with 1/3 cup margarine in bowl, mixing well.
Spoon into baking dish.
Combine remaining 1/3 cup margarine, coconut, pecans, brown sugar and flour in bowl, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: aunt sarah's chicken stew
directions: Mix all together over low heat (real easy to burn) until hot. Serve with corn bread or crackers.
Tastes like you cooked all day!

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with sugar.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts. Serve with sliced apples.

title: high hat tuna souffle
directions: Combine hot milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast onto warm water in a large bowl; stir until dissolved.
Add milk mixture, egg yolks and flour.
Beat until smooth, about 1 minute.
Cover; let rise in a warm place, free from draft, until double in bulk, about 40 minutes.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash in wine until soft; drain.
Mash and mix in cheese, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Add eggs; mix well.
Turn into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cappuccino brownies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coffee granules and vanilla; set aside.
Beat sugar, cinnamon and eggs until sugar dissolves, about 7 minutes.
Fold in chocolate mixture, flour and pecans until just blended.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes; do not overbake.
Cool completely.

title: mongolian beef
directions: Trim all fat from steak.
Cut into 1-inch strips along the grain.
Thinly slice across the grain.
Marinate beef in soy sauce 10 minutes or up to 4 hours.
Slice onions into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Wash spinach and chop into 1 or 2-inch pieces.
Mince ginger. Mince garlic.
Seed and slice pepper thinly crosswise.
Dissolve 1 tablespoon cornstarch in chicken broth (more for a thicker sauce). Heat wok very hot.
Add 1 tablespoon oil.
Stir-fry onions until soft but not brown.
Move to sides of wok.
Add more oil, if needed.
Stir-fry ginger and pepper a few seconds, then add beef and cook briefly.
Move beef to sides of wok.
Stir-fry spinach just until wilted.
Recombine all ingredients in bottom of wok. Add remaining spices and broth.
Simmer about 5 minutes to reduce and thicken liquid, stirring frequently.
Serve with hot cooked rice.
Garnish with shredded carrot, if desired.
Yields 2 servings.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in water and bring to boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add tomatoes, meat, salt, pepper and barley. Continue on low heat for another 1/2 hour.

title: cherry cake
directions: Cream the butter or margarine and sugar together.
Beat each egg in separately.
Stir in flour and salt, adding milk, if necessary.
Mix in cherries (cut in small pieces) and vanilla. Put in 7-inch greased pan and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
(Or, half everything, put in loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Cover bottom with rice.
Lay chicken on the rice.
Mix all soups and water and pour over the chicken.
Cook covered at 350° for 2 hours.
Remove lid or foil the last 30 minutes of cooking time to brown meat.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Place cream cheese in mixer bowl and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour to soften.
Add remaining ingredients and whip until very light and fluffy.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Mix mayonnaise and mustard together.
Cook cauliflower as entire head, slightly underdone.
Frost with mayonnaise/mustard sauce. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° to 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden.

title: macaroni with tarama
directions: Boil macaroni in
salted water.
Drain without rinsing. Return to saucepan; pour in
half	the
oil,
which
has
been heated, over the macaroni.	Fry
onions
in
rest
of
the oil until golden brown.
Dilute
tomato
puree;
bring to boil and add a bay leaf and seasoning.
Add
this to onion.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Add tarama after mashing it with a fork.
Let it boil with the tomato sauce
for	a few minutes.	Pour sauce over macaroni.

title: macaroni and cheese italian style
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Saute onion and garlic until light brown.
Stir in tomatoes, sugar, salt, pepper and basil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Make a paste of water and flour.
Add to tomato mixture, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat. Add grated cheese and stir until melted.
Combine cooked macaroni and place in greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef and gravy
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot on low for 5 to 6 hours (can be cooked all day on low).
Stir before serving.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: chicken new orleans
directions: Place chicken and mushrooms in shallow baking pan.
Mix soup, wine and cheese together and pour over chicken.
Bake in moderate oven uncovered for about 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry beef and sausage with onions and seasonings; drain well. Add tomato paste.
Boil noodles.

title: amy's crab meat spread
directions: Mix seasoning salt, crab meat and cream cheese together until it is well blended. Roll into a ball. Place in a small bowl and drizzle with cocktail sauce. Serve with crackers or cocktail breads.

title: grandma's rolls
directions: Mix yeast
with
cup
of
very
warm
water.
Let sit 5 minutes.
Beat
eggs;
let sit.
Mix sugar, oil, hot water and salt.
Blend
yeast
mixture
with
eggs
and
then with other mixture.
Stir in
cups of flour, blending 1 or 2 cups at a time.
Place
1 cup flour on pastry sheet and about 1/2 cup on top of dough after you turn it onto pastry sheet.
Knead until not sticky
to
minutes).
Add
flour as needed.
Roll about 1/4-inch
thick.
Cut
with
a small cutter and place in greased pan.
(Let
stand
in
refrigerator
if there is time, until about 2
hours
before cooking; it activates
the yeast better.) Let it rise in a warm place about 2 hours (to double) before baking. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: pork ratio chile
directions: Boil pork 2 to 3 hours.
Save water from pork.
Shred meat. Boil red peppers 5 minutes.
Let soak 10 minutes.
Remove peppers from water.
Scrape seeds out.
Puree in blender with pork broth about 4 cups.
Roast green peppers, peel and chop fine.
In pan, add oil, meat, flour, garlic, onion, green chilies and salt. Saute.
Add all of puree broth to meat.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet, stirring until it crumbles. Drain sausage on paper towels, reserving 1/3 c of grease drippings in skillet.

title: carrot cake with pineapple or raisins or both
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Add carrots, oil and eggs. Beat with an electric mixer until combined.
Use undrained pineapple and juice in batter.
Add the nuts.
Pour in two greased and floured 9-inch round baking pans.
Bake for 35 or 40 minutes.
Use cream cheese topping.

title: "tastes like homemade" cranberry relish *
directions: Mix cranberry sauce and drained pineapple.
Add small amount of sugar substitute, if needed.
Sprinkle seed over top and serve for any occasion.
Delish!

title: the best oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, flour and salt.
Sift into butter mixture, mixing occasionally.
Add oatmeal.
Add coconut.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: Add rice, tomato sauce and water to pork chops.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: williamsburg's chownings tavern brunswick stew
directions: Cut chicken in pieces and simmer in 3 quarts water (thin stew) or 2 quarts (thick), until meat is easily removed from bones, about 2 1/4 hours.
Add raw vegetables to broth and simmer, uncovered, until beans and potatoes are tender.
Stir to prevent scorching. Add chicken, boned and sliced and seasonings.
Cook long and slow. Flavor improves when reheated the next day.
Serves 8 to 10. 4:

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together flour and soda.
Mix butter, brown sugar, white sugar, pudding mix and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well.
Gradually add flour mixture, then chocolate chips.
Mix by hand.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Boil 1/2 box acini de pepe (macaroni) until tender. Cool in cold water.

Mix in drained pineapple chunks. In saucepan, add cup of pineapple juice, 3 egg yolks and sugar. Cook on low heat until thick. Cool and add drained oranges, Cool Whip and marshmallows. Mix all together. Let cool in refrigerator.

title: grandma's chicken dish
directions: Combine in a large bowl all ingredients except the corn flakes and margarine.
Spread into a baking dish and sprinkle the top with the crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup margarine broken into bits and pieces.
Bake at 300° until the rice is done.
To keep from burning, place aluminum foil over the top.
Serves 6.

title: christmas punch(a favorite for 30 years)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in the lemonade and strawberries.
Add water and the cranberry juice.
Place 2 trays of ice cubes in punch bowl.
Pour punch over ice.
Slowly pour in ginger ale.
Makes about 25 servings.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a piece of bacon. Cover bottom of flat, greased baking dish (about 8 x 12 x 2-inch) with chipped beef. Arrange chicken breasts on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over all. Refrigerate.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours or longer, uncovered.
I usually cover loosely with foil after 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: tropical sausage kabobs
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the cornstarch and mustard until smooth. Gradually stir in ginger ale and honey until well blended. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly. Alternately thread sausage and fruit onto metal or soaked wooden skewers. Brush with mustard sauce. Grill, uncovered, over medium hot heat for 4 minutes or until evenly browned, basting and turning several times. Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon bread pudding
directions: Mix together juice of 1 lemon, 1 pint of bread crumbs (homemade bread), 1 pint of sweet milk (raw cows milk), yolks of 4 eggs and small lump of butter. Bake in pudding dish or cake pan at 350° until kind of dry on top. When done, remove from oven and add whites of 4 eggs, well beaten with 1 cup sugar and juice of 1 lemon. Return to oven and brown slightly.

title: zesty chili
directions: Place cumin in a 4-quart
nonstick pot and place over medium heat. Cook, stirring frequently for 30 to 60 seconds or until the cumin shells are toasted and fragrant. Pour seeds into small dish and set aside.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes and add butter; mix well.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Pour into baking dish.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix together sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart casserole.
Loosely cover with a lid or plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until boiling.
Uncover.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until "hard ball" candy stage is reached.
Pour this mixture over beaten egg whites while beating with mixer at high speed. Add vanilla and beat an additional 4 to 5 minutes or until candy holds its shape.
Fold in nuts. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper or buttered dish.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Mix all except 1/2 stick of melted oleo and corn flakes.
(This mixture is the topping of the casserole.) Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Keeps well and can be frozen.

title: buttermilk cake filling
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add sugar and butter.
Cook slowly over low heat for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool; add pecans. Spread on cake.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375°.

title: susan's hot lettuce
directions: Tear or cut up a head of lettuce.
Mix hot sauce into mayo to taste.
It will be a pale orange color.
Use as a dip or a dressing.

title: southwest pork chops
directions: Brown chops well on both sides in a large skillet.
Remove chops and pour off most of the fat.
Blend flour into remaining fat.
Put chops back in skillet and sprinkle with the salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Add 1/4 cup of water; cover and cook slowly for 35 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and continue cooking for 15 more minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Drain noodles, dice corned beef, cheese, celery, green pepper and mushrooms.
Add all ingredients to noodles and bake in a 2-quart casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.
Can use a 10 x 12-inch pan if preferred.

title: homemade chocolate pudding
directions: Mix cocoa,
cornstarch
and sugar with milk.
Cook over medium heat
until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla and stir until melted.
Place in serving cups and chill.

title: pudding cake
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix butter, flour and pecans.
Spread in baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together instant pudding with sour cream.
Add frozen orange juice.
Blend well.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: *Mary's version.
Everything else is the same.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix jello and boiling water first and cool.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; combine milk, butter, Wesson oil, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm; add yeast mixture.
Add eggs, then flour; mix to soft dough.
May take a little more flour. Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover with damp cloth
and let rise in warm place until
dough is double in bulk. Punch down, cover and let rise 10 minutes more.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip each round in melted butter and stand on edge around Bundt pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: coke cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Boil margarine, cocoa and Coke together 1/2 minute and add to dry mixture.
Mix buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows; add to other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour mixture into sheet pan.

title: sausage skillet
directions: In extra large frypan (with lid) fry sausage.
Drain if desired.
Over
sausage, cut up potatoes in large slices.
Cut onions and green peppers into rings.
Over top, salt (sparingly). Add
can
of
tomato soup and cook for approximately 1/2 hour on low heat, covered, or until potatoes are cooked.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: In pan, stir together all ingredients except chicken.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cut tips off chicken wings.
Discard.
Cut each wing in half at joint.
Arrange on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 10 minutes, turning once (5 minutes on each side).
Broil 15 minutes more or until chicken is fork-tender, basting with sauce and turning often.
(I turn and baste every 3 minutes, 5 times.)

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Stir 2 or 3 times during the hour.

title: bean dip
directions: Heat chili over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Add cream cheese and hot sauce.
Heat until well blended.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Layer in
a large bowl.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed Heath bars.
Prepare a day in advance.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Stir together 1 1/4 cups sugar, flour and cocoa in a heavy saucepan.
Blend in milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well.
Pile on pie and bake at 350° until brown.

title: casserole bake
directions: Grease baking dish.
Place a layer of potatoes, then of meat, then of onions, celery and pepper.
Repeat until all is used. Cover all with the can of tomatoes.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: nut-date cake
directions: Cream butter well; add	sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs and blend
well.	Flour
dates and nuts; add flavoring and mix well.
Add
flour
a small amount at a time. Beat well each time until
smooth.	Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in moderate oven, maybe a little longer until done.

title: cream puffs
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add salt and sift again.
Combine shortening and boiling water in saucepan.
Keep over low heat until butter is melted.
Add flour, all at one time, and stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball and leaves the side of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Continue beating until a thick dough is formed.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, syrup, vanilla, salt, butter in that order and add pecans last.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Soften margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in 2 tablespoons sugar and pretzels.
Press in pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in oven set at 250°.
(I put it in a heavy oven dish.)
When bark is melted, add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm. Makes lots of cookies.

title: frankie's hamburger casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles
until
tender;
drain.
Brown
ground beef, onion,
and
garlic salt; drain.
Layer noodles and beef in a greased casserole dish.
Mix tomato soup and can of water together.
Pour
over
beef
and noodles.
Layer cheese slices over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ham egg and cheese casserole
directions: Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Tear bread into pieces and drop into egg mixture.
Mix in shredded cheese and ham.
Pour into greased 9x13 pan and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all but last 2 ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cornflakes and oleo.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked green beans
directions: Remove bacon from grease after browning and pour off about 1/2 of grease from skillet.
Brown onions in remaining grease.
Mix together catsup, brown sugar and water.
Pour onion and grease into this mixture and blend.
Put 3 cans of green beans into baking dish.
Sprinkle bacon over top.
Pour catsup mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Season ingredients to taste.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is warm, poke holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand into holes.
Pour topping over cake.
Refrigerate.

title: red potatoes
directions: Mix mayonnaise & ranch dressing together. Cook potatoes (boil). Place in greased casserole dish, pour dressing over potatoes. Cover with cheese, sprinkle bacon bits. Bake 300° until cheese is melted & dressing is bubbling.

title: rich biscuits
directions: Assemble blender.
Heat oven to 450°.
Grease a cookie sheet. Sift dry ingredients together into a large bowl.
Put 1/2 of the cheese into blender container, cover and process at grind.
Empty into dry ingredients and repeat with remaining cheese.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Knead dough very lightly on floured board. Roll out about 3/4-inch thick and cut with floured cutter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Put crackers in a plastic bag.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over crackers; shake.
Let stand overnight or all day.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in the shape of a ball and flatten.
Fry in Crisco.

title: coke cake
directions: Heat butter, cocoa and Coke together until boiling; cool slightly.
Combine buttermilk, soda, vanilla and marshmallows and add to chocolate mixture.
Combine sugar and eggs, stir in flour and add to mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: garlic bread
directions: Slice loaf of bread to your preference.
(I slice off ends, then lengthwise and then into individual pieces.) Mix above ingredients together; spread on bread.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: welsh bread pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over bread chunks.
Add all other ingredients (butter the baking dish).
Sprinkle some cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until crusty on top.

title: cheese danish
directions: Grease and flour 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch glass pan.
Spread 1 package crescent rolls in bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture on crescent rolls and cover mixture with another package of crescent rolls.
Brush with egg white and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until top and bottom are browned.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: frito chili soup
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Put all into a big pot and cook until done.
Add more water if needed.
Serve over Frito chips.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze overnight. Cut into squares and serve.

title: lime punch
directions: Put lime sherbet into punch bowl.
Pour 7-Up or Sprite over sherbet.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
until
blended.
Pour
into buttered loaf pan.	Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: blackberry cobbler paste
directions: Mix well the flour, sugar and milk (makes paste).
Melt stick of butter in pan.
Put berries in pan, add sugar to berries.
Pour paste over berry filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; mix into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough 3 inches apart onto ungreased sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Microwave first 3 ingredients on High for 3 minutes. Then grate paraffin in mixture and stir until melted.
Stir in 2 cups pecans mix well.
Microwave on High for 7-12 minutes.
Checking often to make sure nuts don't burn.
Remove and add soda quickly stir and pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: pickled eggs and beets
directions: Put eggs in saucepan and cover with cold water.
Bring to boil and reduce heat so eggs boil slowly for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; drain.
Rinse with cold water and peel off shells.
Put eggs in large (1/2 gallon) jar with tight fitting lid.
In another saucepan, bring beets, salt, vinegar and sugar to rolling boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add sliced onion and whole cloves.
Pour hot beet mixture over eggs.
Cool, then refrigerate. Beet juice may seem too strong, but will be fine after 1 day.

title: how to boil water
directions: Place water into saucepan and place on stove burner turned on high.
Stand and watch it and it eventually will boil.
Turn your back and it will boil over at once.

title: bean and cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Heat.
To serve, top with additional sliced green onions and Cheddar cheese.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower into small pieces.
Chop onions and radishes; mix with cauliflower.
Mix sour cream, cheese and garlic dressing and mayonnaise.
Pour over mixture and mix well.
Chill overnight and serve.

title: squash dressing
directions: Prepare the cornbread as directed on package and bake.
Saute onion in margarine.
Smash squash; mix with onion, broth, soup and crumbled cornbread.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple ambrosia
directions: Shred apples.
Using a large bowl, put juices in first.
Add apples and bananas to juice to keep from turning brown.
Add other ingredients and chill before serving.
Delicious and refreshing!

title: cocktail pizzas
directions: Toast muffin halves.
Cut in quarters.
Mix tomato sauce, oil, olives and pimento; then add cheese.
Spread on toasted muffin pieces.
Freeze, unwrapped, on cookie sheets.
Then wrap and freeze until needed.

title: party mix
directions: Combine margarine, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and salt; mix well.
Pour cereal, nuts, pretzels and cheese crackers into large zipper bag.
Pour margarine over cereal mixture inside Glad-Lock bag and seal top of bag.
Shake until all are coated.
Pour contents of bag into large size bowl or spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Then store in airtight container.

title: baked eggs
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and beat again.
Put into greased dish, add cheese and ham. Cover with crackers.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add chopped prunes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: chutney cheese canape
directions: In a processor, blend cream cheese, chutney, mustard and curry powder until well mixed.
Scoop out the inside of the pineapple half and fill with cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Save broth.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Saute green pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add tomato, cheese and pimento to cooked spaghetti in broth and stir until cheese melts.
Put all ingredients in casserole and bake at 350° until mixture bubbles.

title: cocktail sausages and cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all together and heat thoroughly.

title: cherry almond cookies
directions: Drop on baking sheet and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: good gravy
directions: Use sausage drippings.
Stir in flour and brown over medium heat.
When thickened, add milk and stir until thick.
Remove from heat and serve over warm biscuits.

title: baked ziti
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Put sausage in a bowl with 1 cup water, microwave for 8 minutes.
Then slice sausage, mix with hamburger, add sauce.
Pour mixture in a 9x13 pan.
Add cooked ziti and mix together.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350 degree for one hour.

title: easy roast
directions: Place the meat in the center of a large piece of aluminum foil in a roasting pan.
Combine the onion soup mix and the undiluted cream of mushroom soup.
Pour the mixture over the meat and wrap the foil over it loosely.
Bake until tender at 325° for 2 hours. You may add potatoes, onions and carrots.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken breasts.
Pound them flat with a mallet. Melt the butter and oil in a large skillet.
Put the flour in a plastic bag and drop the breasts in to coat.
Regulate the heat to moderately high and put chicken breast in skillet.
Cook approximately 3 minutes on each side.
When done, salt and pepper them and put them on an ovenproof dish and into a 250° oven to keep warm while you make the sauce.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Top carrots with pepper and onion.
Pour remaining ingredients over vegetables.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: spoon bread(yields 12 servings)
directions: Scald cornmeal with water, stir thoroughly, then cool.
Add melted fat, egg yolks and milk.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
The batter should be quite thin.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes in moderate oven (350°).
Serve from baking dish with spoon.

title: drunken chicken
directions: Shake chicken pieces in flour, salt and pepper. Saute in butter or olive oil and garlic until lightly browned. Add mushrooms, onion, sweet basil, rosemary, parsley, wine and/or chicken broth (the more juice you have the more liquid to pour over rice) and salt and pepper. Cook, covered, over low heat (simmer) for approximately 1 hour.
Thicken gravy only
if desired.
Serve over rice.

title: kansas city salad
directions: Line bottom of 9-inch dish with lettuce.
Layer green pepper, red pepper, celery, onion and frozen peas.
Mix mayo with sugar; spread over salad mix.
Top with cheese, then bacon.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Colorful for holiday dish.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour.
tags: cream of onion soup or mushroom soup

title: grilled pineapple chicken
directions: Preheat grill or broiler.
In a shallow pan, combine marinade mix with pineapple juice, soy sauce and brown sugar.
Place chicken in marinade, pierce deeply with a fork and marinate for 15 minutes, turning occasionally.
Remove chicken to grill or broil for about 5 minutes per side or until thoroughly cooked; baste occasionally with remaining marinade.
Serve with sliced orange. Serves 4.

title: dressing
directions: Cut bread into large cubes and place in large pan.
Bake in oven at 250° until dried out.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Brown pepper and onion in pan; add ham and cook a few minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: red chile
directions: Brown meat in olive oil in a hot skillet.
Then add flour, garlic, chile powder and chile piquin and salt.
Mix all ingredients well with meat and oil but be careful not to let it burn.
Then add water to desired consistency.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: special cranberry mix
directions: In a food processor, grind cranberries and oranges.
Remove. With shredder blade, shred apples.
Put all into large pot.
Cook until mix is like applesauce.
Sweeten to taste.
Good with yogurt and over ice cream.

title: braised cabbage
directions: Heat oil in a 12 inch skillet over moderate heat for 1 minute. Add onion and saute for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add cabbage, toss for 2 minutes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover skillet.
Cook for 40 minutes, stirring often.
Add tomatoes.
Salt and pepper (to taste).
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes longer.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes. Grease two bread pans and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: scotchies
directions: Sift flour, soda and
salt together.
Cream shortening, add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir
in flour mixture, oats and pecans. Drop by spoonfuls on
greased
cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Dice rhubarb and cover with warm water until you are ready to use.
Combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon to make crumb mixture.
Press half the crumbs in a greased 9-inch baking pan.
Then drain rhubarb and place on top of crumbs.
Cook white sugar, water, cornstarch and vanilla until it thickens. Pour cooked mixture over rhubarb and top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: the norwegian pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg thoroughly.
Add eggs, vanilla, diced apples and chopped nuts. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mixture evenly in pan.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Pie makes its own crust.

title: crunchy turkey salad
directions: Divide turkey, celery, pickles and onion between 2 large bowls.
Mix mayonnaise, salt, curry powder and pepper.
Toss half of the mayonnaise mixture gently with each turkey mixture. Refrigerate no longer than 12 hours.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 hours.
May be prepared in advance.
Freezes well.

title: loaf bread
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and salt.
Add yeast and water.
Add beaten egg.
Add flour.
Knead, let rise, put in tin, let rise and bake.

title: unbaked caramel cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring all the while.
Remove from heat and add pudding mix (dry from package).
Add oatmeal.
Cool 15 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Mix together and heat.

title: marinade for beef
directions: Combine marinade ingredients in a shallow glass dish large enough to marinate.
Add meat to marinade, turn to coat other side.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate up to 24 hours, turning meat occasionally.
Grill or broil meat to desired doneness.
Slice London Broil thin across the grain of the meat.

title: parmesan-curry popcorn
directions: Mix margarine, cheese, salt and curry powder.
Pour over popcorn; toss.
Yields 12 cups; 120 calories per cup.

title: blueberry tea cake with crumb topping
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and milk to butter and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients.
Add in blueberries.
Spread in a greased and floured 8 or 9-inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle with crumb topping.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oriental garden toss
directions: Combine green onions, soy sauce, water, sesame oil, Equal, garlic powder and red pepper flakes in screw-top jar; set aside.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk; cook until a drop forms a soft ball in cold water or 232° on thermometer.
Add butter, salt and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and satiny.
Pour into buttered 10-inch glass pie pan.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Pour enough cold water on beef in 4-quart pot with 3 tablespoons white vinegar.
Cover and soak overnight.
Next day, rinse beef and refill pot with clean, cold water.
Bring to boil and rinse once more.
Refill with cold water.
Bring beef and water to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer (with onions whole and peeled), until beef is tender, about 2 hours.
Add cabbage, carrots and potatoes 20 minutes before beef is done and simmer until done. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix in small bowl.
Serve on rye crackers.

title: salmon with mint marinade
directions: Place salmon steaks in ungreased rectangular baking dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat remaining ingredients except bay leaf thoroughly; stir in bay leaf and drizzle over fish.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour, turning fish over after 30 minutes.
Remove fish from marinade; reserve marinade.
Grill fish, uncovered, about 4 inches from hot coals 10 to 15 minutes, turning over once and brushing with marinade frequently, until fish flakes easily with fork.
Heat remaining marinade to boiling.
Remove bay leaf. Serve with fish.

title: white frosting
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Add granulated sugar and milk, stirring until well blended. Over medium heat, bring to boiling, stirring.
Remove from heat; let cool slightly.

With portable mixer at medium speed or wooden spoon, gradually beat 1 3/4 cups confectioners sugar into warm mixture, beating well after each addition until frosting is thick enough to spread and barely holds its shape.
If frosting seems too thin to spread, gradually beat in a little more confectioners sugar.
Add vanilla.

title: chicken scaloppine
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half and pound with wooden mallet until very thin.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Saute chicken over moderately high heat, a few pieces at a time, until lightly browned on both sides, adding more butter as needed.
Remove to heated dish.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients in a medium bowl.
Line 9 inch pie plate with first crust.
Add filling.
Top with other crust. Crimp and cut.
Make 4 slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 25-30 minutes.

title: possum cream pie
directions: Mix together flour, oleo and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt the stick of butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all the ingredients together except for the cheese and pour into dish with melted butter in it.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and top generously with the grated Cheddar cheese, then put back into the oven for about 5 more minutes.

title: cinnamon yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in milk.
Add sugar and 1 1/2 cups flour.
When bubbly, add salt, eggs, shortening and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Knead; let rise until double size.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with melted butter and cinnamon.
Roll like jelly rolls.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place in greased pans.
Let rise until double in size.
Just before baking, pour caramel syrup over it (made by bringing to boil the brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter and water). Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 18 rolls.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain; add onion, chili powder and salt.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer crushed tortilla chips, beef mixture, mashed beans and Cheddar cheese as listed.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 10 to 15 minutes.
When serving, garnish with shredded lettuce, sliced tomatoes and sour cream.

title: "one bowl" brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large bowl at High for 2 minutes.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Stir in sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir flour and nuts.
Spread into a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudge crumbs.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat in sugar; spread half in each crust shell.
Sprinkle half nuts on each pie.
Spread half pie filling in each and top with Cool Whip.

title: coconut pie
directions: Pour in deep pie crust.
Cook at 350° until done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: pineapple ham glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
About 30 minutes before ham is done, remove from oven.
Score surface.
Spoon glaze over entire ham.
Return to oven, basting occasionally during last 30 minutes.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Put butter, sugar and milk on stove; boil 1 minute.
Take off heat; add chocolate chips.
Stir until thick.
Spread on any cake, warm or cool.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Place chicken pieces in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix the chicken broth with soup; heat in saucepan.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Mix melted margarine, flour and buttermilk; pour this over chicken and soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Brown at 450° for at least 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: pineapple-lemon pies
directions: Mix and pour in cooled, cooked pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Heat ingredients in a medium size pan until doughy consistency.
Cool and store in a small plastic bag or jar. Children will be amazed to discover that combining these things over heat will turn into play dough!

title: crock-pot stuffing
directions: Use large crock-pot; spray or grease.
Cube bread.
Add celery, onions and pepper.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups water and add along with melted oleo.
Toss lightly.
Put in crock-pot on low for 4 hours.
Serves 8 to 10 people.
Nice for holidays when oven is full.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Beat eggs at high speed of electric mixer until very thick, about 10 minutes.
Lower mixer speed to medium and gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in half and half, evaporated milk, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Add strawberries and food coloring to desired color.

title: consomme
directions: Mix and cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: Drain and combine fruit. Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine the dry pudding mix with milk and orange juice concentrate.
Mix with rotary beater.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold into fruit mixture. Cover and chill.

title: tortilla and chicken bake
directions: Saute onion.
Add soup mix, chilies, chopped chicken and water chestnuts.
Cut tortillas into fourths.
Alternate mix, cheese and tortillas, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients except meat in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Simmer a few minutes; brown meat on both sides.
Place single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Pour half of sauce over ribs; cover with foil and place in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Remove foil, baste and continue baking another 15 to 20 minutes. The sauce recipe is enough for 2 pans of ribs.

title: puff balls
directions: In a heavy pan bring water to a boil.
Add butter and stir until butter melts.
Add flour and salt.
Reduce heat and stir continuously.
Cool and add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg is added, until batter is smooth and shiny.
Turn half batter into mixing bowl.

title: grandma babcock's biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir cranberry sauce into jello mix and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into
mold and chill until served.
Perfect for Thanksgiving and Christmas dinners.

title: date nut balls
directions: Dissolve margarine, sugar, egg, vanilla and dates.
Cook about 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add to this mixture 1 cup nuts and 2 cups Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls and roll in fine coconut.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in hot oil until tender.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Baste meat with sauce prior to cooking.

title: date and nut loaf cake
directions: Pour boiling water over first two ingredients and let cool. Cream sugar and butter, then add egg, flour and nuts or fruit. Bake slowly at 350° for one hour.
Makes two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaves.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl and chill.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Make sure eggs and butter are at room temperature. Cream sugar and butter together. Add eggs and milk to sugar mixture. Blend well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to mixture. Blend well. Add vanilla and coconut. Blend well. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Remove	crust
from bread.
Roll flat with rolling pin. Spread each slice with cream cheese (that is softened).
Roll into
log shape.
Place
in
refrigerator until chilled.
Cut each log
into 3 or 4 pieces; dip each piece in melted butter and
sugar and cinnamon that has been mixed together.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper in butter until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir to separate meat particles.
Add soups, water and garlic.
Heat.
Blend with 1/2 cup cheese and cooked spaghetti in a 3-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes, or until bubbling and hot.

title: chocolate pie(over 50 years old)
directions: Heat milk in saucepan on low heat.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs.
Add small amount of milk, if necessary, to blend well.
Add slowly to hot milk, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and cool.
Pour into baked pie shell. Prepare meringue; spread over chocolate and brown.

title: crumb cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for only 20 minutes.
Top with crumb mixture and continue baking 10 to 15 minutes longer or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool and top with confectioners sugar.

title: portuguese soup
directions: In a large soup pot, heat oil over medium-high heat and saute the onions and garlic until golden.
Add the crushed tomatoes, carrots, cabbage and beef stock.
Simmer 10 minutes; then add the sausage, cayenne pepper, salt and black pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 2 hours, stirring in the kidney beans about 15 minutes before completion.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Optional:
2 cups rice may be substituted for noodles.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger with green pepper.
Blend in soup and milk. Combine with cooked noodles in casserole dish and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Do not alter any of these ingredients.
It takes this special combination for the special flavor.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, water and cocoa to boil.
Remove from heat. Add sugar, flour, salt, eggs, sour cream and baking soda while hot.
Pour into greased cookie sheet (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch). Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: common market broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into florets and the stalks into small pieces. Steam until bright green, but still crunchy.
Drain and cool.
Add the next 5 ingredients (vegetables) to broccoli.
Mix the mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and Good Seasons dressing mix together and pour over broccoli mix.
Marinate for at least 3 hours.
(I prefer overnight.)
You may add cauliflower, if desired.

title: german apple cake
directions: Pare the apples and cut into thin slices. Mix the 5 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples and toss. Set aside.

title: colorful pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, cook onions and peppers in butter or oil until tender.
Stir in parsley flakes, oregano, pepper, salt and garlic.
In large bowl, combine eggs, grated Parmesan cheese, corn and the cooked vegetable mixture (onions and peppers).

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese, Marshmallow Creme, orange rind and spices.
Wash, core and slice apples into wedges.
Dip wedges in pineapple juice to prevent discoloration.
Serve apple wedges with dip.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all the ingredients using the spices in desired amount. Keep in refrigerator and use on fish or potatoes.

title: sally lunn
directions: Measure 1/2 cup water into mixing bowl.
Add yeast, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth (100 strokes).
Cover.
Let rise until very light (1 hour).
Beat down; pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Let rise to within 1-inch of top of pan (45 minutes).
Bake until golden brown and crusty.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat well with all seasonings.
Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Arrange layers of noodles, meat, cheese and sauce; repeat with cheese layer on top.
Sprinkle oregano over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry salad(congealed salad)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch container.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
With mixer blend cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Pour on top of congealed layer.
Allow to chill before serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir dry pudding mix into pineapple; mix well.
Blend/fold in Cool Whip and other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix the boiling water and the oats; let stand.
Mix the remaining ingredients together, then add the oat mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oma's apple cake(oma means grandmother in germany.)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Mix in flour and baking powder.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Pour in cake pan.
Place slices of apple in batter.
Top with cinnamon sugar mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes.

title: deviled drumsticks
directions: Parboil chicken legs in 2 cups water with onion, carrot and marjoram for 1/2 hour.
Do not overcook.
Remove drumsticks from pot.
Add 1 cup water, salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon aromatic bitters.
Mix flour with small amount of water from pot and add to pot until gravy is thickened; set aside.
Score drumsticks and rub with prepared mustard mixed with 1 teaspoon Angostura Bitters.
At serving time, heat gravy and broil drumsticks under the broiler until crisp and brown.
Remove to heated platter and brush with butter.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: gazpacho
directions: Place first 3 ingredients into blender and blend briefly.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
You may top with onion and chopped eggs or olives if desired, when serving.

title: regina's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; add veggies.
Mix in seasoning and dressing. Chill.
Add tomato just before serving.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Combine coconut and margarine.	Reserving 2 tablespoons coconut
mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom and up side to rim
of
9-inch pie plate.	Chill.	In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice, fruit cocktail, almonds and cherries.	Mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into prepared
crust.
Garnish with reserved coconut and additional fruit,
if	desired.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt together margarine and brown sugar.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending with margarine and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry to wet mixture. Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Toothpick check for last 5 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Gently combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Refrigerate overnight (a must).

title: hamburger corn bread pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening; add seasonings.
(May use more chili powder if you want it really spicy.)
Stir in tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add beans.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Place broccoli and sour cream in a food processor or blender container; process 5 to 10 seconds or until broccoli is finely chopped.
Stir broccoli mixture and Cheez Whiz in a 1-quart bowl. Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring every minute.

title: creamy cheesecake apple squares
directions: Mix oleo and cake mix until crumbly; set aside 2/3 cup for topping and add to it cinnamon and brown sugar.
Save for later. Put cake mix and oleo mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan (ungreased). Press down well.
Put sliced apples over cake mix.
Mix the cream cheese, one package at a time with one egg, beating well after each addition.
Beat in sugar.
Add sour cream and vanilla. Spread this mixture over apples.
Sprinkle topping mixture on top.

title: cherokee chicken
directions: Heat oil and butter in a 12-inch skillet.
Add chicken; cook until golden brown on all sides.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add green pepper, garlic and onion; cook until soft.
Add vermouth, cranberries, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 25 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot curried chicken dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until blended and heated thoroughly.
Serve dip hot with chips or bland crackers.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine thawed (slushie) lemonade, Cool Whip and milk.
Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours and serve.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Blend in flour and chicken bouillon cubes.
Gradually stir in milk, stirring continuously until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken and mushrooms. Arrange rice in nonstick 8-inch casserole dish.
Spoon chicken mixture over rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: aunt marge's baked beans
directions: Fry and drain hamburger, bacon and onion.
Add barbecue sauce, ketchup, mustard, molasses, chili powder and pepper.
Stir until mixed.
Add all 3 cans of beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ranch stew
directions: Melt fat in large kettle.
Cook beef, onion and green pepper, stirring occasionally until meat is browned and onion and pepper are tender.
Add liquids to meat and cook until liquid is reduced to about half.
Add corn, beans, tomatoes, chili powder and salt. Heat to serving temperature.

title: corn, peas and bean salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper; bring to a boil. Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: goodnight cookies
directions: Beat egg whites, sugar and baking powder until stiff.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Turn oven off.
Drop cookies by teaspoonfuls onto ultra heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Place on oven racks.
Remove from oven in the morning.

title: quick chocolate-cola cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl; beat at low speed with electric mixer until blended; set aside.
Bring cola to boil in small saucepan over medium heat.
With mixer on low speed, gradually pour hot cola into cake batter.
Increase speed to medium; beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a wood pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.

title: butter crusted chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and paprika in melted butter.
Coat each piece of chicken with the mixture by brushing it on.
Place in foil lined pan and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for an additional 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dream whip salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 cup hot water.
Add 3/4 cup pineapple juice. Cool.
Let mixture get syrupy.
Add Dream Whip, cottage cheese (small curd) and pineapple.
Chill until thick. Stir occasionally. Makes large dish.

title: caramel tassie cups
directions: Mix cream cheese (room temperature), 1 cup margarine and flour all together as you would a pie crust.
Roll into a ball and chill dough at least 2 hours.
Then, roll into balls; shape into tassie pans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
When baking tassies, remove from oven before done; press pastry down gently and place back in oven to finish baking time.
Cool completely.
Heat together in double boiler Kraft caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk until smooth. Keep heating on low while filling cups 3/4 full.
Let cool until firm.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Use a very large mixing bowl.
Mix together shortening and margarine.
Blend in sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder; add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip together and refrigerate.
Serve with fruit.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Add water. Stir constantly over medium heat until mix is thick and clear. Remove from heat.
Add food color and jello.
Stir well.
Cool. Hull berries.
Chop.
Drain.
Place in shell.
Pour jello mix over berries.
Chill and top with cream.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in water and mix in flour mixture.
Add buttermilk and mix well.

title: toffee bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pat with hands on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut when it comes from oven into bars.

title: pepper jelly
directions: In blender, place green pepper, hot pepper and cider vinegar. Blend for a few seconds.
In a 6-quart saucepan, combine pepper mixture and sugar.
Rapidly bring to a rolling boil that cannot be stirred down.
Remove from heat for 10 minutes.
Skim off froth. Stir in Certo and seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 6 to 7 half-pints.

title: dirty rice
directions: Put rice in a 2-quart casserole.
Saute onion and garlic in oleo or butter.
Add onion and soup to rice.
Add pepper and mix. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Stir once or twice during cooking.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange
chicken
in
a
lightly greased shallow baking dish. Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine, stirring well. Spoon
sauce
evenly over the chicken and sprinkle with the stuffing
mix.
Drizzle
butter
over the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine melted margarine with crushed pretzels.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Put in baking dish.
Top with 3/4 cup catsup, 1/2 cup brown sugar and a little mustard (mixed).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients; add eggs.
Combine next four ingredients and mix well with sugar, oil and egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop with teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten each cookie with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Do not overbake!

title: crab meat on english muffins
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread
over 12 halves of English muffins.
Cut them in quarters.
Brown under broiler.
Good to make ahead and freeze.
Put
out
as needed.
Put frozen under broiler until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain first 4 fruits. Combine in large bowl and set aside. In medium mixing bowl, beat pudding mix, milk and orange juice for 2 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Mix well.
Spoon over fruit to which apple has been added.
Toss to coat fruit. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours. Will keep several days refrigerated. Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: flemish beef-and-beer stew
directions: Cut beef into 1/2-inch slices; cut slices into 2-inch strips. (For ease in cutting, partially freeze beef about 1 1/2 hours.) Cut bacon into 1/4-inch pieces; fry in Dutch oven until crisp. Remove bacon with slotted spoon; drain on paper towels.
Pour off fat and reserve.
Cook and stir onions and garlic in 2 tablespoons of the reserved bacon fat until tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove onions.
Cook and stir beef in remaining bacon fat until brown, about 15 minutes.
Stir in flour to coat beef; gradually stir in water.
Add onions, beer, bay leaf, brown sugar, salt, thyme and pepper.
Add just enough water to cover beef if necessary.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Stir in vinegar; sprinkle with bacon and parsley.
Serve with noodles.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 5 minutes; cool.
Add remaining ingredients and enough white flour to make a dough.
Knead well. Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again. Shape into 3 loaves.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 50 minutes more.

title: shortbread
directions: *If you cannot buy superfine sugar, put sugar in a blender and grind until you get a finer consistency.

title: e-z chicken
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprinkle dry soup in pan.
Add raw rice.
Place chicken pieces over rice.
Mix mushroom soup and water together and pour over chicken.
Salt and pepper chicken and bake 1 hour at 350°, longer if you want chicken browned.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 5 minutes.
Slice zucchini and brown in garlic butter.
Place half of browned zucchini in baking dish.
Add layer of hamburger mixture, then remaining zucchini.
Cover with your favorite cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Combine soup, oil, vinegar, brown sugar, Worcestershire, garlic powder and hot sauce.
In a 3-quart oblong dish, arrange chicken.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Spoon soup mixture over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes, until chicken is no longer pink.
Serves 4.

title: bernice's orange drop cookies
directions: Milk may be added if not right to spread.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine all ingredients, except flour, with the yeast.
Mix well in a mixing bowl.
Add flour to form a stiff, yet soft, dough, beating after each addition.
Cover and let rise until light and doubled in size (1 hour).
Stir down dough and turn into well-greased casserole dish.
Let rise until light (about 40 minutes).
Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, and taco seasoning.
Spread into tray. Spread salsa over the top, then add shredded cheese. Chop veggies and put on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; mix well.
Add catsup and rice wine vinegar to already mixed sugar and cornstarch; blend well. Add water and mix well with a whisk.
(This can be done in the pan you will cook in.)
Cook on high until thickens; remove and serve. Yummy with spareribs, chicken, fish or vegetables.

title: rum cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add vanilla.
Beat in eggs and stir in flour.
Bake in greased stem pan for 1 hour at 325°. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Pour on icing while still hot.

title: meryl's cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine tomatoes, celery, onions, salt and sugar.
Heat to boiling point; let simmer.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat with electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Bake in a greased 8-inch square pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake this stiff batter.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: This is a recipe that is wonderfully elastic.
It all depends on what you have in the refrigerator and how many you need to serve.
It is a delicious way to use leftover vegetables that aren't headed for the soup pot.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in crock-pot.
Do not dilute soups.
Cook on low 6 hours.
Remove lid the last hour.

title: party cheese ball
directions: All cheeses should be at room temperature.
Blend well and shape into ball.

title: strawberry yogurt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Generously grease bottoms & sides of 2 round pans with shortening. Beat cake mix, water, oil, egg whites and yogurt in a large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds then on medium speed for 2 minutes pour into pans.

title: great rice and beef casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Brown beef, onion and green pepper in a skillet together; drain oil.
Combine all ingredients except cheese in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Boil turkey until done. Let cool. Slice into small pieces in baking dish. Cover with cheese. Mix soup with 2 cups turkey broth. Pour over turkey and cheese. Take 4 tablespoons butter and melt in a
bowl. Add stuffing to it. Pour over top of turkey. Don't cook the stuffing, just mix with butter. Bake until stuffing turns golden brown.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Mix all ingredients except rolls.
Mold 2 crescent roll triangles into a square (4 squares).
Fill each square with 1/4 of chicken mixture.
Fold and seal crescent rolls.
Follow baking directions on package of crescent rolls.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet tammi chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring mixture to a boil and beat well until very smooth.
Pour over cake while cake and frosting are still warm.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Beat eggs and molasses.
Mix sugar and lard, then combine. Sift together 3 times the baking powder, flour, salt, soda and spices; add milk.
Put together and beat thoroughly.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° to 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Light oven; get utensils and ingredients.
Remove blocks and toys from table.
Grease pan and crack nuts.
Measure 2 cups flour; remove baby's hands from flour and wash flour off him/her. Remeasure flour.
Put flour, baking powder and salt in sifter.
Get dust pan and brush up pieces of bowl baby knocked onto floor.
Get another bowl.
Answer door bell.
Return to kitchen.
Remove baby's hands from bowl.
Wash baby.
Answer phone.
Return to kitchen. Remove 1/4-inch salt from greased pan.
Look for baby.
Grease another pan.
Answer telephone.
Return to kitchen and find baby. Remove his/her hands from bowl.
Take up greased pan and find layer of nut shells in it.
Head for baby, who then flees, knocking bowl off table.
Wash kitchen floor, table, walls, dishes and baby. Call grocery store to order cake.
Take 2 aspirin and lay down.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Simmer 30 minutes, put through food mill.
Add 1/2 c. olive oil.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: mrs. kimbro's special chicken
directions: Wash and season chicken the night before cooking.
The next day, place chicken under boiler and brown lightly on each side. Remove chicken from the broiler and add juice from chicken to hot water.
Baste chicken with water and juice mixture.
Place chicken in oven at 350° and baste every 15 minutes with mixture.
Cook until almost done.
Mix 1/2 can of cream of chicken soup with remainder of juice/water mixture.
Pour over chicken and cook until done.

title: lemon pepper catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place fish in a single layer in an oiled baking dish.
Drizzle butter over the fillets and sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes.
Fillets are done when a fork slices through the thickest part of the fillet with little resistance and the fish flakes easily.
Serves 6.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg and 1/3 cup sugar.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips and set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix together flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour and soda.
Cut shortening into flour with a fork. Add buttermilk; mix well.
Turn dough onto well floured surface. Knead until dough is no longer sticky.
Roll dough to a 1/2-inch thickness and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake in a well-greased pan for 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: peas and peanuts
directions: Cook peas until done.
Place in cold water until cool and drain.
Fresh peas may be used.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill. Garnish with yellow and red pepper rings.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to mixture along with buttermilk.
Work together with a spoon or hand until flour is moistened.
Cover bowl and put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Mixture will keep for quite some time.
In fact, they're better if fixed several days ahead.
Roll out, cut and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: corn chowder
directions: Heat margarine in large saucepan until melted; stir in onion and celery.
Cover and cook until veggies are soft, then add flour and stir for about 1 minute longer.
Continuing to stir, add milk gradually; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook, stirring continuously, until mixture is smooth and thick.
Add remaining ingredients; keep stirring and cooking until all ingredients are combined and mixture is hot.
Makes about 3 servings, 1 cup each. Takes about 1/2 hour to prepare.

title: hamburger heaven
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet with the chopped onion.
Add remaining ingredients in layers in order given.
Add pepper to preferred taste.
Rinse out tomato can with 1/4 cup of water and pour it over the entire dish.
Cover when steaming ; turn to simmer and cook for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend Oreos in blender until they're crushed fine.
In separate bowl, combine pudding and milk, then blend in butter, sugar, cream cheese and whipped cream.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine in large pot of boiling water 14 minutes (no longer).
Drain but do not rinse.
Place in large bowl.
Add chopped vegetables and 3/4 bottle of spices.
Mix very well.
Add salad dressing.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Next day stir well again before serving.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 12-inch buttered pan. Brush top with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole(teacher favorite)
directions: Mix together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered, until brown.

title: oreo delite
directions: Melt margarine; mix with Oreos.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix
cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour in dry pudding mix and 2
cups
milk.
Beat
until
real thick, about 4 minutes. Pour over pressed cookies.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle top with crumbled Oreos.

title: classic onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan that holds at least 4 quarts. Add onions; cook over medium heat 12 minutes. Stir often. Add sugar and cook, stirring for 1 minute. Add broth; cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 12 minutes. Add brandy; cook 2 minutes longer. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar, vinegar and milk.
Pour over salad ingredients 1 hour before serving.
You may substitute cauliflower for the broccoli.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Thicken with cornstarch and milk if desired. Heat on low only till cheese melts.

title: corn chowder(low-fat)
directions: Preheat large, heavy saucepan over medium heat for about 1 minute. Spray it twice with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Saute the onion for about 5 minutes until translucent. Add 4 cups of the corn and saute for 4 to 5 minutes until it softens a bit.
Add 2 cups chicken stock and cook until the corn can be mashed easily with a fork, about 20 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain all of liquid from pickles.
Slice pickles in thick slices and layer in gallon jar, alternating layers of pickles and sugar.
Set jar on plate in refrigerator for three weeks.
Turn jar upside down every three days.

title: never fail blueberry cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in blueberries.
Grease a 9 or 10- inch Bundt Pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: birds nest
directions: You will need 1 (9-inch) round or square baking dish.

title: do not peek (pork chops or chicken)
directions: Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle raw rice in bottom of pan.
Pour melted butter and milk evenly over rice.
Mix soups together (without water) and spoon over rice.

title: san francisco tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add vinegar.
Cool.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, onion and celery; refrigerate.

title: fish fritters
directions: Cook fish.
Remove all skin and bones.
Mash fine.
Beat egg yolks until light and thick.
Add flour.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, parsley and fish.
Beat egg whites and fold into fish mixture.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil (360° to 370°).
Cook until golden brown.

title: chicken jambalaya(microwave)
directions: Soak lid of the Magic Clay Simmer Pot for 10 minutes in cold tap water.
In bottom of Magic Clay Simmer Pot, place Creole jambalaya mix and water.
Mix well.
Add chicken pieces.
Cover with water soaked lid.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes. Rearrange chicken pieces and cover with lid.
Microwave on 50% power for 25 to 30 minutes or until rice and chicken are done. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Thoroughly brown meat on all sides in hot fat, turning often. Add boiling water, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion, bay leaves and seasonings.
Cover and simmer (don't boil) for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves and garlic clove.
Add carrots and onions.
You may also add cubed potatoes if you wish. Cook covered another 30 minutes or until vegetables are done. Remove meat and vegetables and thicken liquid for gravy.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomatoes.
Gently mix.
Shape into 6 1/4-inch patties.
Grill burgers 8 minutes, turning after 5 minutes.
Grill tomatoes 5 minutes; turn once until bubbly.
Top burgers with tomatoes.
Serve on buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans. Shape into a ball and roll into pecans. Chill until ready to serve. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and vanilla.
Cook and remove to cool; add butter or oleo and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350° in 9-inch pie shell.

title: shrimp party spread
directions: Toss together shrimp, green peppers, olives, pimento, blue cheese, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Gently blend in sour cream.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Cut chicken in thin slices.
Roll in flour.
Melt butter and saute until brown.
Remove, then add wine, soy sauce, mushrooms and par-cooked carrots.
Add all to baking dish and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix margarine, flour and nuts in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Whip cheese, Cool Whip and sugar. Spread on top of crust.

title: pink pineapple punch
directions: Combine first four ingredients and stir well.
Add ginger ale at last minute.
Makes 32 (4 ounce) punch cup servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Break bread into bite size pieces and spread in a 1 1/2-quart casserole pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and pineapple.
Pour over bread and mix until all bread is covered.
Pour melted butter over and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients for cake as you would cake batter. Spread batter in greased baking pan.
Beat egg whites for topping; add sugar (last 2 ingredients).
When stiff, spread smoothly over top of cake batter.
Baking all at once, bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown on top and bottom.
This crisp topping keeps cake from getting soggy.
Cut in squares and serve with sweetened berries or other fruits.

title: layered pesto appetizer
directions: On a large round platter, mold cream cheese into a seven-inch circle.
Top with a layer of pesto about the same thickness as the cream cheese.
(You will not use all of the pesto which can be frozen for later use.)
Sprinkle tomato pieces over pesto until well covered.
Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers or bagel chips.

title: e-z candy
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and milk 9 minutes.
Pour in buttered pan and frost with chips and garnish with nuts.

title: christmas cathedral cookies
directions: Melt 6 oz. chocolate chips and 1/4 cup butter in microwave. Cool, add egg well beaten, powdered sugar, marsh mellows. Separate into 2 equal parts. Roll each part in nuts or coconut on wax paper.

title: cheez whiz chicken
directions: Flatten or thin chicken by slicing with a knife to round out and make it easier to roll up similar to a cabbage roll.
Place 1 tablespoon (heaping) Cheez Whiz in the center of the chicken and roll up, ensuring that ends are tucked in.
Roll chicken in Ritz cracker crumbs and place in loaf pan or baking dish small enough that chicken pieces are touching together.
This keeps the cheese in place.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes, depending on the amount of chicken, until done.

title: french black bottom pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, cream the butter. Gradually add sugar, creaming until light.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in egg. Continue beating for 3 minutes at medium speed. Spoon into crust. Prepare mix according to package directions except in place of 2 cups milk, use 1 1/2 cups.
Let stand until thick.
Pour over mixture. Chill until firm. Top with Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lazy lady cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients (sift together) in large bowl.
Add liquids and mix with a fork.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together, then add large can crushed pineapple (drained) and chopped nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done. Pour pineapple juice over cake while still warm.

title: potato donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into hot grease.
Drain, then coat with powdered sugar.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix well. Add dry ingredients. Chill several hours. Roll out in your favorite shapes. Bake at 350° until very lightly brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cracker candy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Cover with saltine crackers.
In a saucepan, mix next 2 ingredients and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over saltines.
Cook in oven for 5 minutes.
Take out and straighten crackers.
Quickly pour over this the bag of morsels.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Spread with a knife.
Refrigerate until chocolate set.
Peel off aluminum and break into pieces.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chiles rellenos casserole
directions: Stuff each chile with a strip of cheese.
Arrange chiles in a buttered casserole dish in as many layers as necessary.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, half and half and eggs.
Beat slightly until mixed.
(Batter will appear slightly lumpy.)
Season with salt and pepper and pour over chiles.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Five minutes before serving, sprinkle top of casserole with grated cheese and sunflower seeds.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: noodle pizza
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add green pepper, ground oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes. Cook and drain noodles.
Place noodles in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish, spreading evenly.
Pour the hamburger mixture over the noodles.
Place sliced onion over entire surface. Put grated Mozzarella over surface.
Place pepperoni slices over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let sit for 5 minutes, then cut into squares.
Serve with green salad.

title: seven-up date bread
directions: Bring dates, 7-Up and baking soda to boil; set aside and let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add to date mixture; beat well.
Pour into greased small loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
