Bring to full boil for one minute.
Serve over two slices of angel food cake with vanilla ice cream between slices.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Combine coconut, crumbs, pecans and sugar.
Mix with Eggbeaters.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into pastry lined 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (or until set).

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and flour and cream until fluffy. Add syrup.
Beat well.
Add salt and eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla and stir.
Divide filling into 2 pie shells; then add 1 cup pecans to each pie.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until set.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder thoroughly.
Add egg.
Mix again. Mixture will be crumbly.
Place cherry pie filling in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan.
Cover with flour mixture. Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream, if desired. Other fruit fillings may be substituted for cherry filling.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked custard-sugarless
directions: Combine egg and Sweet 'N Low. Slowly add milk and vanilla, blending well. Top with a sprinkling of nutmeg. Bake in pan of hot water (1/2 way up sides of custard cups) in moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour or until mix does not adhere to knife.

title: miniature ham biscuits
directions: Slice all rolls lengthwise.
Place ham and cheese on rolls. Put top on ham and cheese.
Melt butter, mustard, onion and garlic. Brush this on rolls.
Wrap these in aluminum foil and heat to 350° until warm.

title: cream baked trout
directions: Clean the trout, put in pepper and salt and close them.
Place the fish in a pan with just enough cream to cover the fins and bake fifteen minutes.

title: korean barbecue meat
directions: Cut
beef in thin slices.
Add sugar and oil; mix well. Combine
soy
sauce,
pepper,
chopped
onion, chopped garlic, sesame seed and flour.
Add to the meat;
mix well.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Broil over charcoal or pan-fry.

title: hawaiian fruit dip
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Blend in sour cream.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Cover and chill 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fresh-pack dill pickles
directions: Wash and scrub cucumbers carefully.
Cut 1/4-inch slice from blossom end of each cucumber.
Mix water, vinegar and salt in a Dutch oven; heat to boiling.
Place dill head and onion slice in each of 6 hot quart jars.
Pack cucumbers in jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover with boiling brine, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Wipe rims of jars.
Seal and process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: lemon shortcake with cream cheese topping
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix, milk, sugar, margarine and lemon peel until soft dough forms.
Gently smooth into a ball on lightly floured cloth-covered surface.
Knead 8 to 10 times.
Pat dough to 1/2-inch.
Cut with floured 3-inch round cutter.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Stir in a small amount of milk, if needed, to make creamy.
Top warm cakes with cream cheese mixture and serve.

title: apple sara
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with pie crust.
Slice apples into crust.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over top.
Cover with top crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Glaze.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat butter in rectangular pan, 13 x 9-inch, until melted.
Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper. Coat chicken with mixture.
Place chicken skin side down in pan. Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage and onion in small amount of water for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix with white sauce.
Put into a 9 x 12-inch casserole in layers, alternating cabbage mixture, crumbs and cheese.
Top with crumbs and bake, uncovered, at 375° until hot.

title: molasses sugar cookie
directions: Mix well, chill.
Form in 1 inch balls, roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: microwave 9 minute coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk in a 2-quart microwave dish.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir and microwave 3 more minutes, then add small amount hot mixture into yolks.
Return to hot mixture and add coconut.
Microwave 3 more minutes on High.
Add butter and vanilla and pour into baked pastry shell.
Put meringue on pie and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350° in regular oven.

title: hot water bread
directions: Mix together.
Boil a small pot of water.
Pour into batter until the mixture gets gummy and sticks together.
Stir constantly.
Make little pones and drop into hot skillet of grease.
Brown evenly on both sides.
Serves six.

title: broccoli with lemon sauce
directions: Wash and separate stalks into sections.
Place in boiling
6 quarts of water; salt to taste.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
In same pan, place oil and garlic.
Heat until bubbly. Add broccoli and sprinkle with lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook, covered, for 1 minute or until heated through.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer sauerkraut and noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer on the onion and corned beef.

title: chocolate cake with cherries
directions: Pour oil in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tilt pan to cover bottom.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with chocolate or cream cheese frosting.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Cream mixture (1/2 c. sour cream, 1/2 c. mayo, and 1/2 package of taco mix).

title: angel food delight
directions: Mix milk with pudding; fold in Cool Whip and oranges and mix well.
Break up cake in bottom of dish and spread pudding mixture over cake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and place in casserole. Heat 1 can celery soup, milk and cheese. Add 2 beaten eggs to mixture and pour over the broccoli. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients together and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Decorate with cherry or nut.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Crumble
butter, brown sugar and flour together and set aside 2
cups.
To
remaining mixture add eggs, milk, vanilla and baking soda and beat well.
Pour into well-greased 18 x 12 x
2-inch pan.
Sprinkle
crumbly mixture on top and sprinkle Heath Bits
'O Brickle over crumbly mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Cream Cheese Mixture:
Beat together the softened cream cheese and butter.
Add the sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla; beat until smooth and set aside.

title: broiled salmon burgers
directions: Combine bread crumbs, egg whites, chili sauce, lemon juice, onions, cheese and pepper in medium size bowl and mix well.
Flake salmon into bowl and blend gently.
Form salmon mixture into 5 patties.
Melt butter in nonstick skillet; pan fry the patties over medium-low heat about 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
(Patties may also be brushed with melted butter and oven-broiled 3 to 4 inches from heat.)
Serve on toasted whole wheat buns with extra chili sauce, if desired.

title: hot dogs stuffed with dressing
directions: Slit hot dogs lengthwise on top halfway through.
Mix the dressing according to directions on package.
Stuff each hot dog, in the slit.
Wrap a piece of bacon around the hot dog with a spiral wrap to hold it together.
Bake at 350° until bacon is crispy or done as you like it, 20 or 25 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend first 10 ingredients in saucepan until smooth; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer 2 minutes.
Place 1/4 cup chicken, 2 tablespoons of cheese and 1 tablespoon of sauce on each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spread remaining sauce over enchiladas.
Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Finely shred crabmeat.
Mix crabmeat well with the bread crumbs moistened with the milk, the yolks of the hard-boiled eggs rubbed through strainer, mustard, salt, pepper and melted butter.
Fill the timbales or small dishes with the mixture.
Sift very fine bread crumbs lightly on top; dot with butter.
Brown quickly in a hot oven, being careful they do not burn.

title: orange-cranberry relish
directions: Put orange quarters with peels and cranberries in food processor.
Add sugar.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: ripe cucumber pickles
directions: Peel cukes, take out seeds, and cut into pieces.
Cover with salt and let stand over night.
Drain and rinse with cold water, drain again.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.
Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat.
Add sugars and vanilla; blend well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour; blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 40 minutes. Turn out onto wire rack.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over top. Let stand until cool.
Cut into squares.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Three teaspoons mixed with water make a cup of tea. Store tea in a sealed jar.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add sour cream and flour alternately.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.
Pat out or roll on floured board.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 400° for 8-10 minutes.
Makes 7-8 dozen cookies.
If desired, sprinkle colored with colored sugar before baking or ice when cool.

title: oreo cake (dirt cake)
directions: Crush Oreos (reserve 6 or 7 to top cake).
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Pour over Oreos.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Add 3 tablespoons milk if too lumpy.
Spread over Oreo mixture.
Mix pudding according to box. Layer over cream cheese mixture.
Next top with 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crushed Oreos over Cool Whip.
If using mini Oreos, can replace whole Oreos on top to decorate.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cake mix and eggs.
Pat dough onto greased pizza pan to make crust.
Cook at 450° for 8 minutes.
Do not cook longer or it will be hard.
If you want it browner, put in broiler for 1 to 2 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Spread cherry pie filling or strawberry glaze on crust.
Arrange pineapple, bananas and grapes on top.
If pie filling is used, put small amount over fruit.
If glaze is used, cut berries in half and place cut side down.

title: lace cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls on a well buttered Teflon pan.
Cook in oven for 5 minutes.
Remove carefully.
Let cool for 1 to 3 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Put all ingredients together.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Let cool and spread on layers.

title: cereal
directions: Pour cereal into a bowl.
Pour milk in the bowl.
Add sugar sometimes.

title: eight layer quiche
directions: Saute pepper, onion, mushrooms, sausage, ham, bacon and chicken together in a large skillet.
Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain and place in the bottom of the unbaked pie shell.
Top with cheese.
In a separate bowl, beat the eggs.
Add half and half and the flour to the eggs and mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and continue baking 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Serves 6.

title: tropical punch
directions: Pour in punch bowl and serve.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar and butter in large bowl.
Add cooled, scalded milk, then add yeast, eggs, 2 cups flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Beat real good.
Add remaining flour; knead for 2 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and refrigerate all night to raise.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream until smooth.
Add egg yolks (set aside whites), beating until well blended.
Add soda and vanilla to buttermilk.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cake mixture.
Bake at 350° in tube pan, approximately 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Place grated cabbage, chopped onions and peppers in a bowl. Combine equal amounts of sugar, vinegar and 1/4 cup oil in a pot. Heat to melt sugar.
Pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle some celery seed over cabbage.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop or grind cabbage, onions and peppers together.
Add vinegar to come to top of mixture.
Add all other ingredients; let come to a boil.
Can at once.
Yields approximately 20 pints.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottoms of three 9 inch round cake pans with waxed paper.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening together.
Beat in one egg at a time, beating 2 minutes after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add coconut and flavorings.
Mix well.
Bake in a tube pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not preheat oven. The oven must be cold when cake is put in to bake.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Use 12-inch round pizza pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes (until light brown).

title: kool-aid playing dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, alum, Kool-Aid, vegetable oil and boiling water in a large bowl.
Knead until a good consistency is attained.
Store in an airtight container or in locking plastic bags.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking or roasting pan. Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Makes about 8 servings.
Great with grilled steaks or hamburgers!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut or tear into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
(I cook the rice in the chicken with broth for a little while.)

title: ice cream
directions: Beat
the chilled evaporated milk until foamy.	Add the Cool Whip and beat.
In another bowl, blend together the sugar and eggs.
Add the vanilla and the fruit or Butterfingers and beat. Pour
everything
in
freezer
and finish with milk, if needed. Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add oil and blend at medium speed of mixer until dry ingredients are moistened.
Add pumpkin and mix again.
Add beaten eggs and blend 1 minute (do not overbeat).
Pour batter into 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: congealed cottage cheese salad
directions: Boil together for 3 minutes the juice and pineapple and jello. Cool mixture.
Add cottage cheese and chopped nuts.
Last, fold in whipping cream which has been whipped and sweetened to taste. Congeal in shallow pan or molds.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Cook cake mix by box instructions.
Cool.
Mix pudding and cream cheese together.
Spread over cake.
Put drained pineapple on top of pudding, then
Cool Whip on pineapple, coconut on Cool Whip and nuts on coconut.

title: chili
directions: Sear meat and drain off fat.
Add all other ingredients except masa
harina
and
simmer
minutes.
Skim
off any grease. Mix
masa
with
1/4 cup warm water and add to chili. Simmer another 15 minutes.
Better the next day.

title: fly cemetaries(or eccles cake or raisin squares)
directions: Wash the raisins.
Let them stand an hour so they will swell some.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: easy potato soup
directions: In a large boiler mix cream of chicken soup with 2 cans of water.
Peel and slice carrots into thin slices.
Add to soup. Peel and dice potatoes.
Add to soup.
Add celery and onions and slight pinch of Italian seasoning.
Salt and pepper to taste. Boil on low setting stirring frequently until potatoes and carrots are done.
About 30 minutes.
If soup gets too thick you can add more water, but don't thin it down too much because the thicker it is the better it is.
Goes great with grilled sandwiches.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Put potatoes and onion into a 3-quart saucepan and barely cover with cold water.
Add salt.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Mash potatoes in their liquid.
Add butter, evaporated milk and water. Stir and add a little more water if soup is too thick.
Reheat to scalding.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chopped parsley.
Top with bacon pieces or chopped ham, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes 5 servings.

title: party salmon mold
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine all ingredients, except pecans and parsley.
Mix well.
Chill several hours.
Shape in form, ball, etc.
Sprinkle with pecans and parsley.
Chill.

title: easy cream cheese appetizer
directions: Place the blocks of cream cheese on plate.
Spread pepper jelly on cheese.
Serve with crackers.
(I like it best with Triscuits.)
Enjoy!

title: nana's peas(my favorite)
directions: Cook peas, butter, salt and pepper together until tender.
Add half and half cream to this.
When bubbling again, thicken to gravy stage with water and flour thickener.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in tight fitting container.
Stir 2 to 3 teaspoons in a cup of boiling water.

title: slush punch
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients until Jell-O and sugar are dissolved. Then add remaining ingredients.
Freeze in small portions.
When ready to use, scrape into a slush.
Add 4 or 5 quarts ginger ale or 7-Up.
Use flavor of Jell-O for color desired.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Turn oven to 200°.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: fruit and tea punch
directions: Combine sugar, lemon juice and orange juice in punch bowl. Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in pineapple juice and tea. Serve over crushed ice in tall glasses.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling together, adding pecans last. Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°
and bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer. Outer edge of filling should be set while the center is still slightly soft.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook all vegetables and allow to cool.
Combine sugar, flour, mustard, vinegar and water in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Cool. Pour over vegetables.
Best if made the day before.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a six-quart pot, saute sausage and remove.
Add oil and saute green pepper, garlic, celery and parsley over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes with liquid, chicken broth and onions.
Stir in spices.
Add rice, sausage and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
When most of liquid is absorbed add meat and cook until seafood is done.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 to 5 quarts.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: no-cook strawberry freezer jam
directions: Measure sugar into separate bowl. Stir sugar into 2 cups crushed berries.
Set aside for 10 minutes, stirring.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Top with Miss Melba's Meringue (Melba Meadows).

title: skillet green peppers
directions: In 10-inch skillet melt butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except tomatoes and croutons.
Cook over medium heat. Stir occasionally, until peppers are crisply-tender (6 to 8 minutes).
Add tomatoes.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Sprinkle with croutons and serve immediately.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Brown bacon and onion together; add to crock-pot with other ingredients.
Cook on low 4 to 9 hours.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Spread cherry filling in 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Spread dry mix over cherries.
Sprinkle nuts on top of cake mix.
Drizzle butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: hors d'oeuvre cheesecake
directions: Combine cheeses and taco seasoning; beat well.
Add the eggs; stir in half of the sour cream.
Fold in the chilies and red pepper.
Pour into a greased 10-inch spring-form pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until set.
Combine the remainder of the sour cream and salsa; spread over the cheesecake.
Bake for an additional 5 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Cover and chill for at least 8 hours.
Garnish with chopped fresh tomatoes, sliced olives, shredded cheese or sour cream.
Serves 12 to 18.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt and scalded milk slowly.
Bake in moderate oven until knife comes out clean.

title: mamma mia minestrone(soup)
directions: Put the onion on the cutting board. With a knife, cut the onion in half from the pointed end to the root end. Pull off the papery skin with your fingers. Place the onion halves flat-side down on the cutting board and cut off the root ends. Chop the onion halves into small pieces. Put the onion pieces in a large saucepan.

title: divinity candy
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to 26° on candy thermometer or until small amount of mixture dropped in very cold water forms a hard ball.

title: cooked mayonnaise
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and mustard in saucepan. Gradually add water and vinegar. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils. Boil 1 min. Remove from heat. Pour into bowl. Beat in egg yolks with rotary beater. Continue beating, adding vegetable oil a little at a time. Chill before serving. When using, modify as desired with whipped cream. 2 c dressing.

title: blueberry monkey bread
directions: Thoroughly grease a tube pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll each piece in sugar-cinnamon mixture. Arrange about 1/4 of the biscuit pieces and the blueberries in an even layer in pan.
Place blueberries between biscuit pieces, creating a mosaic effect.
Repeat 3 more times with remaining biscuits and blueberries, covering the blueberries in 1 layer with biscuits in the next layer to avoid a column of blueberries.

title: peaches and cream
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder.
Combine egg, milk and melted butter or margarine.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drain peaches, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
Chop peaches.
Sprinkle atop batter.
Beat together cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar and reserved peach liquid.
Pour atop peaches in pan.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and the cinnamon.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serves 9.

title: quick shrimp gumbo(low-fat)
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion and garlic in oil for 2 minutes. Stir in sausage. Cook for 2 minutes or until sausage begins to brown. Add green pepper. Cook for 2 minutes. Stir in the tomatoes, broth, seasonings and hot pepper sauce. Bring to a boil. Cook, uncovered, for 2 minutes. Stir in shrimp. Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer or until shrimp turn pink. Stir in rice. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand for 5 minutes or until rice is tender. Discard bay leaf. Yield: 4 servings.

title: heavenly strawberry cheesecake
directions: Combine crushed graham crackers and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: curry and rice
directions: Cut meat into cubes and finely chop onions.
Chop other vegetables in pot.
Saute meat and onions in oil, stirring until onion is lightly browned.
Add other vegetables.
Add 3 1/2 cups water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Break curry sauce mix into mixture, stirring until completely melted.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve hot over rice.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Pour boiling water over All-Bran; let sit.
Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in buttermilk, Bran Buds and All-Bran. Add dry ingredients.
Will keep in refrigerator covered for a week or so.
Bake at 350° to 375° until brown, 20 minutes or so.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Mix until smooth; chill in refrigerator.
Form into small rolls about size and length of a finger.
Bake in 350° oven about 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 50 to 60 fingers.

title: june's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter into small crumbs. Spread 3/4 C on bottom of baked pie crust.
Save the rest to sprinkle on meringue.

title: bruna flarn(swedish cookies)
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar thoroughly.
Add nuts and then flour.
Shape small balls of dough (1/2 teaspoon size) on well-greased cookie sheet.
Leave plenty of room as they spread while baking.
Bake at 400° for 4 to 5 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Shape over rolling pin for curved shape.
Looks like a Pringle chip.
Has lacy appearance and crisp.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown together onion, garlic and oil.
Simmer sauce for 45 to 60 minutes.
Layer sauce, noodles, sour cream and cottage cheese by spoonfuls.
Finish with sauce and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add salad oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Chopped nuts may be added if desired.
Makes 5 small loaves.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Put zucchini in food processor.
Mix crushed zucchini, oil, sugar and eggs.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Oil and flour pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: minnie hot dogs
directions: Get a greased pan. Open crescent rolls.
Wrap rolls around hot dogs.
Cook 30 minutes.
Eat!

title: ham and cheese pecan spread
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk. Stir in remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Spoon into 8 inch pie plate.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot or at room temperature with assorted crackers.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Combine other ingredients.
Add to meat and cook until done.
Serve over noodles.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant, slice and cook in salted water until tender; drain.
Mash eggplant.
Add 1 cup cheese and butter.
Let melt. In 1 1/2-quart baking dish, mix crackers, milk, eggs and salt. Add eggplant mixture and mix well.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry butter
directions: In blender or food processor, blend together butter, medium strawberries, powdered sugar and grated peel of 1 lemon.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and place in a 3 to 4-quart baking dish.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom soup over vegetables.
Cut butter up over top.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: no-bake peach pie
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Dump into pie pan and press to shape.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool while assembling filling.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix together hot water, shortening and sugar. Set aside to cool. Dissolve yeast and teaspoon sugar in lukewarm water. Add yeast mixture to first water mixture; add lightly beaten eggs and salt, then the flour 1 or 2 cups at a time. When thoroughly mixed, cover tightly and place in refrigerator overnight. Remove dough from refrigerator; punch down and knead a few times.

title: panic day cake
directions: Arrange pie filling evenly in 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle evenly with cake mix.
Dribble margarine evenly over mixture.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts and sprinkle over top.
Cook 10 minutes on High, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking time.
Rest 10 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add this mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add flavorings and pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand about 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: marinated shrimp and vegetables
directions: In 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, combine vegetables and shrimp.
In small bowl, combine remaining
ingredients; mix well. Pour lemon mixture over vegetables and shrimp.
Cover.
Chill several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
To serve, spear with toothpicks.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: robert redford dessert
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Partially cook and drain broccoli; add onion mixture, rice, cheese and soup and stir to blend.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until cheese browns and bubbles.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except Sour Cream Sauce.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place meatballs on rack in broiler pan.
Bake at 375°
for 20 minutes.
Keep warm.
Prepare sauce.
Serve hot.

title: martha's co. casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in butter.
Stir in salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Remove from heat; cook and drain noodles.
Combine cottage cheese, onion and green peppers.
Spread half the noodles in a 3-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with remaining noodles.
Pour ground beef mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken and dressing bake
directions: Mix stuffing with 1/2 can of chicken soup, broth and eggs. Spread in 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch buttered baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine remaining soup with 1/2 cup chicken broth. Pour over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Note:
Roasted salted peanuts may be used and added as the last ingredient.
Omit salt if peanuts are salted.

title: mom's tuna patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make sure they are mixed well. Shape into patties.
Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in a skillet. Cook patties on medium until slightly browned.
Makes 4 patties. You can substitute finely ground saltine crackers for the quick oats, just lower the amount of salt used.
These make a good change from hamburgers and are just as tasty!

title: chocolate banana bread
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Stir in pecans and chocolate. Blend bananas, eggs and shortening or oil.
Add to flour mixture and mix until flour is moistened.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Sear pork chops in hot skillet.
Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Cover tightly; simmer for about 30 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: taco salad pie
directions: Bake crust according to package directions.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of the cheese evenly over bottom of baked crust.
Cook bacon until crispy, drain on paper towels.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon drippings from skillet.
Add onions and cook until tender, add tomatoes, 1/2 cup picante sauce, cumin and oregano.
Cook over high heat until most of liquid is evaporated.
Spoon tomato mixture into crust, top with bacon and remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted.
Peel, seed and slice avocado into wedges and arrange over pie.
Drizzle with remaining picante sauce. Garnish with sour cream, olives, lettuce, etc.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: parmesan taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in barbecue sauce and 1/2 cup cheese.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and place in a greased baking dish.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Combine sugar, salt, shortening, 3/4 cup water and 1 cup flour in a mixer bowl; beat until smooth.
Add yeast mixture; mix well.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on a floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease surface.
Let rise, covered, in a warm place for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Divide dough into 2 portions.
Roll each portion into a thin circle on a floured surface.
Fit into 2 greased pizza pans.
Brush with oil.
Spread with tomato sauce. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni, mushrooms, olives and seasonings.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dadson delightful brunch
directions: Saute meat, onions and mushrooms.
Beat eggs, spices and milk. Line pan with bread.
Layer with meat mixture.
Pour egg mixture over all and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp vesuvius
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease individual ovenproof dishes. Place scallops in dish.
Arrange shrimp on top.
Place cheese on top of shrimp.
Make Bechamel sauce by melting butter.
Add flour and whisk well.
Slowly add milk and broth, whisking all the while.
Add Worcestershire, garlic and horseradish until smooth. Pour Bechamel sauce over cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes or until bubbly on top.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Mix the herbal stuffing with the melted oleo. Spread over cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry flavored Jell-O in boiling water and let cool.
Stir in pineapple and the next ingredients and spoon into a lightly oiled 4 cup mold or an 8 x 10-inch casserole dish. Cover and chill.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
If desired, garnish with fresh cranberries and orange rind strips.
Yields 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) generously.
Beat all ingredients vigorously with spoon for 30 seconds.
Pour in pan.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan and remove.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Crust:
Spread cookie dough on a round pizza pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown onion, then add and brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce, tomato paste, refried beans and olives.
Use 1/2 Cheddar cheese and 1/2 Brick cheese mixed.
In a baking dish, layer in order:
chips, meat mixture, cheese and sour cream until dish is full.
Bake at 350° until cheese is lightly browned.
Serve with extra sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: quick taco dip
directions: Layer 1:
Heat beans a little and spread all over large serving plate.

title: veggie bites(kid tested recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 450° (for kids, wait until they are coating veggies to preheat).
Brush bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with 1 tablespoon of melted margarine.
Beat together egg and water with a fork in shallow dish.
Mix flour and salt together in another shallow dish.
Dip about 1/4 of vegetables into egg mix.
Remove 1 vegetable piece at a time with slotted spoon, fork or fingers; roll in flour to coat and place in pan (but not on top of each other).
Repeat with remaining veggies.
Pour remaining margarine over each veggie piece in pan.
Bake, uncovered, turning once, until veggies are crisp-tender and coating is golden brown (about 10 to 12 minutes).
Sprinkle lightly with Parmesan if you like.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Let stand overnight.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: fried garbanzo beans
directions: Chop and saute onion and green pepper until tender, then add chorizo, ham and garbanzo beans with liquid and saute over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat for approximately 1 hour.
If you see that the liquid is drying up too much, cover and simmer for the remaining time.
This is good served over white rice.

title: bacon potato soup
directions: Cook bacon.
Save 2 teaspoons bacon grease to add to soup. Saute onions and celery.
In heavy pot, crumble bacon.
Add onions and celery.
Add bacon grease and salt.
Mix 1/2 milk with flour; add to other ingredients.
Add remaining milk and onion salt.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add next five and beat 2 minutes. Then stir in cranberries.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Bake at 325°.

title: sweet and hot ribs
directions: Bake ribs in
oven 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Mix all ingredients and then
brush on ribs frequently with 1/2 of mixture. Bring other 1/2
of
mixture
to	boil
and
pour over ribs to serve.

title: chicken in silver
directions: Cut 6 (18-inch) squares of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Peel and slice potatoes, carrots and onions.
Place equal portions of chicken pieces on each piece of foil.
Salt and pepper chicken. Top each portion with 1 tablespoon barbecue sauce.
Divide vegetables equally among portions of chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot each portion of vegetables with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Bring edges of foil over chicken and vegetables and seal tightly.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: snicker salad
directions: Chop Snickers bars and add apples, Cool Whip and pecans and stir together.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook until thick.
While hot, add marshmallows and beat until dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Cut in fine pieces (do not use the juice). Combine with whipped cream.
Let set overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: the best crawfish
directions: Melt margarine in large heavy skillet over low heat.
Saute green onions, garlic and celery 5 minutes or until tender.
Add crawfish; stir and saute 5 more minutes.
Add soup, sour cream, cheese spread and Creole seasoning.
Mix; simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Stir crawfish mixture and cooked noodles together in a 2-quart dish.
Heat in 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve hot with a green salad and French bread.

title: layered ground beef casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Plate alternate layers of ground beef, potatoes and onions in a buttered dish.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Place pieces of butter on top.
Dilute soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over the mixture.
Cover and cook done (1 hour) at 350°.
Brown the beef before you alternate it in the casserole with the onions.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Melt shortening in a large skillet; brown and cook meatballs.
Remove meatballs; put in a casserole or slow cooker.
Pour fat from skillet.
Put drained pineapple and green pepper over meatballs.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press rolls into large cookie sheet and bake according to directions.
Whip together cream cheese, mayonnaise and party dip. Spread mixture on cooled crust.
Top with any type of veggies desired.
Once pizza is topped, cover with plastic wrap and press veggies into mixture so it holds together.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: deer steaks
directions: Beat steaks with back of butcher knife or glass Coke bottle to tenderize.
Dip into salt-pepper-flour mixture and fry in 2 tablespoons of oil or fat over medium-hot burner.
Slice onions, thinly over steaks and pour in 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: potatoes in foil
directions: Place foil in pie pan.
Layer potato slices by alternating with onions and slices of margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cook in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Great with barbecue!

title: paul prudhomme's mandeville mardi gras chili
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients in a small bowl and set aside (seasoning mix).
In 12-quart heavy saucepan, melt margarine over high heat.
Add 3 cups onion and 2 cups bell pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in 3 tablespoons of seasoning mix.
Cook until vegetables are soft and brown (about 11 minutes).
Set vegetable mixture aside.
Cook meat and 3 tablespoons of seasoning mix on high until meat is brown (about 14 minutes).
Add reserved vegetables to meat.
Add garlic and remainder of the seasoning, onions, celery and green pepper.
Cook 7 minutes.
Add tomatoes and puree and beef stock.
Cook, covered, about 2 hours.
Add molasses and green chiles and cook about 15 more minutes.

title: simply super salmon spread
directions: Drain, debone and skin salmon.
Crumble finely with hands. Add cream cheese, green onions and horseradish.
Combine well. Put in an attractive bowl; sprinkle with pecans.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: lemon pies(makes 2 or 3 pies)
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk 2 minutes on low speed.
Add lemonade mix (dry).
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells. Refrigerate or freeze.

title: good cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Make in little balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Press with fork and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Stir every now and then.

title: strawberry yogurt pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Put all ingredients in bowl. Beat at medium 3 minutes. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake until toothpick comes out clean.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Combine ingredients and beat well.
Pour into 2 ice cube trays.
Cover with foil or Saran Wrap after frozen.
Allow to stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: holiday relish
directions: *We have used 1/2 white and 1/2 brown.
Makes a different tasting pickle.

title: rhino soup
directions: Boil rhinoceros until tender.
Remove skin, debone and dehorn. Cut rhino into small bite size pieces.
(This should take about 2 months.)
Add enough brown gravy to cover (about 1/2 of a tanker truck).
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer 4 to 6 weeks. This serves 5800 people.
If more are expected, add 2 rabbits.
Do only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: summer sausage and cheese treats
directions: Slice summer sausage in thin slices.
Cut a slice of American cheese in 4 sections.
Take a cracker, bagel or English muffins (split bagel, cut muffins); place a piece of summer sausage on top of cracker, then a piece of cheese.
Microwave on High (max power) 35 to 40 seconds or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Simmer all ingredients (except chops) in uncovered saucepan. Place chops in bowl.
Cover with sauce.
Cover bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Arrange chops in shallow baking dish. Pour sauce over.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine instant rice (right from the package), milk, salt, cinnamon, sugar and raisins in a saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; boil slowly for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Slowly pour hot mixture into slightly beaten eggs.
Beat vigorously.
Add vanilla.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and let cool 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in stick of butter.
Add cooked rice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart baking dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt martha's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition (medium speed).
Put vanilla and lemon into milk. Fold in flour alternating with milk.
Spoon into 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on rack.
Dust with powdered sugar before serving.

title: shirley mckenzie's chicken and rice
directions: Boil chickens in salted water.
Use broth for cooking rice. Heat cans of soup with can of milk.
Combine soup with eggs, mushrooms, pimento, almonds, onion juice, rice and seasonings to taste.
Cut up chicken into pieces and combine in a casserole dish with soup mixture.
Top with potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 16.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make night before and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: susanelli
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use flour needed.
Work the dough until smooth and firm, then roll it up bit by bit.
Cut in one inch long and 1/2 inch thick and fry.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and flour into mixing bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan, blend Coca-Cola, butter, shortening and cocoa.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add to flour mixture. Beat eggs; add.
Mix soda with buttermilk; add.
I mix flour, sugar and marshmallows together before I add hot mixture.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 40 minutes.

title: pecan crumble sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl combine flour, sugar and allspice; mix well.
With pastry blender cut in butter until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Coarsely chop pecans; toss in crumb mixture.
Set aside.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut sweet potatoes in 1/4 inch diagonal slices, starting with potatoes. Layer with 1/2 cup pecan/crumb mixture, potatoes, crumb, etc. Drizzle with maple syrup.
Bake lightly covered with foil 45 minutes, if raw potatoes, 30 minutes, if canned.
Remove foil. Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese garlic bread
directions: Cut bread (lengthwise) in half.
Spread 1/2 stick margarine on each half.
Sprinkle generously with garlic powder, Parmesan cheese and Romano cheese.
Garnish with parsley flakes.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: congealed salad
directions: Prepare jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Place in refrigerator until cool, but do not gel.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash, do not peel, one potato per person.
Slice 1/4-inch slice and soak in cold water for at least 20 minutes.
Melt 4 tablespoons margarine on a cookie sheet.
Drain potatoes and pat dry.
Place potatoes on cookie sheet in single layer, coating both sides with margarine. Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a 425° oven and bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned on each side.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O and Knox gelatine in water, sugar and lemon juice.
Cool slightly.
Add fruits, nuts and vegetables.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Whisk together all ingredients and spoon into a 9-inch pie plate or 2 cup casserole.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven or until lightly browned.
Garnish with paprika and/or parsley, if desired. Serve hot with wheat or rye crackers or Melba toast rounds.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add pumpkin.
Mix in remaining ingredients, flour last.
Bake at 350° for 17 minutes.

title: baked apple squares
directions: In a large bowl beat together sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add oil and vanilla; mix.
Fold in walnuts and apples.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes. (Serve hot or cold.
Top with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.)

title: pizza casserole
directions: Grease dish, mix everything (save some cheese for top of casserole).

title: fruit torte
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and line a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save a little for topping.
Cream sugar, margarine and eggs and place over crumbs.
Cover with any juicy fruit (I like peaches or nectarines).
Cover with whipped cream (Dream Whip) and sprinkle with the saved crumbs.
Put in refrigerator for about 4 hours to set.
The longer it sets the better, juice soaks into cookie crumbs.
No sugar in crumbs or fruit.
Good dessert to make the day before you need it!

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Heat 4 tablespoons of bacon grease or oleo in large iron skillet.
Remove grease or oleo from heat and pour in ingredients.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes and serve.

title: swedish steak
directions: Season meat with the seasoning ingredients.
Can add other seasonings to your own liking.
Place meat into baking pan.
Mix the tomato sauce and mushroom soup together; pour onto the meat. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serve with rice.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Microwave or boil chicken until cooked. Cut up into bite-sized pieces.
Pour soups into casserole dish. Do not add water!
Stir in chicken, cheese and water chestnuts. Mix well.
Place in oven and bake 15 minutes.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Makes 2 large loaves, using 10 1/4 x 3 5/8 x 2 5/8-inch pans. Use wax paper or tinfoil in bottom of pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: eggplant parmesan (low-fat version)
directions: Preheat the oven to 400° and put the oven rack on the bottom of the oven.
Spray a cookie sheet with olive oil spray; set aside.
Peel and slice eggplant 1/4-inch thick.
Dip the eggplant slices in the beaten egg or beaten egg white, then into the bread crumbs.
Place eggplant on a baking sheet and spray with olive oil spray.
Put the eggplant in the oven and bake for 15 minutes. Remove from oven; spray tops again with olive oil, then turn slices and spray again with oil.
Bake another 5 minutes and remove from the oven.
In the bottom of a baking dish, spread a thin layer of marinara sauce.
Top with a layer of eggplant until the eggplant is used.
End with a layer of sauce.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cooked through.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: slushy punch
directions: Stir sugar and 2 3/4 cups water until sugar dissolves.
In a blender, blend bananas, half of pineapple juice and orange concentrate.
Blend until smooth.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in remaining pineapple and lemon juice.
Transfer to baking pan. Freeze.
To serve, let mixture stand at room temperature.
Spoon into punch bowl.
Pour Sprite down side of bowl and serve.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until almost tender. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Cook and stir until smooth. Drain macaroni.
Combine with butter mixture in a large bowl and mix well.
Stir in milk and 4 cups cheese.
Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving (yields 12 to 16 servings).

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Combine Bisquick, corn meal and sugar in bowl.
Add eggs and milk until well blended, mix in oleo.
Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch greased pan or muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in pan, but less in muffin tins.

title: frozen banana punch(serves 50)
directions: Boil sugar and the 6 cups of water for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Place in punch bowl and add 2 large sized bottles of ginger ale or Sprite.

title: gram's butterscotch cookies
directions: Cook butter and sugar over low heat until bubbly.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: your basic macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare white sauce by combining Butter Buds, flour, salt, pepper and slowly adding skim milk.
Stir with a wire whisk until smooth and thickened.
Set aside.
Place half of the cooked macaroni in the bottom of a 2-quart glass casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Sprinkle with half of the onion, salt, pepper and cheese.
Repeat.
Pour sauce over the casserole. Drizzle 1 tablespoon liquid Butter Buds over the top. Sprinkle remaining cheeses over this.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Yields 8 servings.

title: avocado fruit compote
directions: Mix lemon juice and grapefruit juice.
Add apple, banana, grapefruit, orange, avocado and honey.
Chill before serving. Serves 4.

title: baked chicken
directions: Roll chicken in cracker crumbs. Place on cookie sheet that has been covered with aluminum foil. Season. Place in oven at 350° for 10 minutes. Take back out of oven and pour melted butter over chicken. Place back in oven for about 1 hour.

title: mounds cake icing
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa together.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Add water to desired consistency.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Stew chicken, seasoned with salt, pepper, a stalk of celery, a chopped onion and chopped carrot, if desired.
Remove chicken, saving broth.
Debone chicken and stir back into broth.
Bring to simmering point over low heat.
Drop tortilla pieces several at a time into broth.
Simmer for 15 minutes until tortillas are tender.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and taco mix.
Spread on plate.
Top with lettuce, tomato, cheese and black olives.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix in 8 x 8-inch pan or 2-quart dish.
Top with grated cheese, crushed cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Place in loaf pan, dot with butter and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until it puffs up.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut or chop broccoli and mix with other ingredients. I usually put the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together first and then mix in the rest of the ingredients. Stays well in the refrigerator.

title: candied grapefruit rind(perfect at christmas)
directions: Peel grapefruit and cut rind in quarters. Let stand overnight in salt water (1 tablespoon salt to quart of water). Drain; wash thoroughly and cut into strips. Simmer in clear water, changing water several times until the grapefruit rind has no bitter taste (six or more times). When the rind is tender, drain and cook in a sugar syrup of 2 parts sugar to 1 part water until rind is transparent.

title: grandma's fruit cake
directions: Sift the flour once; measure.
Add baking powder and spices; sift 3 more times.
Cream the shortening; add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, fruits, nuts, honey, molasses and cider.
Add flour gradually.
Put in 5 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: devil's food pudding cake
directions: In large bowl, combine the cake mix, oil, baking powder and eggs.
Prepare pudding mix according to directions on the package. Add the pudding to the cake mixture and stir together.
Pour into well oiled 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes on lowest shelf in the oven.
Sometimes I mix the chocolate chips and nuts with the batter and frost the cake with buttercream frosting.
It is yummy either way, but has a tendency to fall.
If this is a problem, make cupcakes instead.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg; add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix well, stir in zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Chill dough for 2 hours, then drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: tuna salad sandwiches
directions: Mix tuna, onion, sandwich spread, eggs (chopped up) and pickle relish in a bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes about 10 sandwiches.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Beat sugar, oil, catsup and onion with electric mixer 15 minutes or until thick.
Add vinegar and celery seed.
Beat until mixed well.
Keeps well.

title: oatmeal-chocolate chip caramel bars
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well (reserve 1 cup). Press the rest into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes. Top with nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix caramel topping and flour until smooth. Drizzle over top. Sprinkle with reserved 1 cup oatmeal mixture.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes longer.

title: fat-free golden cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray two 8 or 9-inch pans with Weight Watchers buttery spray.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Stir in applesauce and milk and beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat additional 2 minutes.
Pour into pans and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans 5 minutes, then turn out on racks.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice in medium bowl. Do not peel apples. Dice apples in bite size pieces. Add apples to mayonnaise mixture; stir to coat well. Add celery, walnuts and raisins.
Toss gently to mix well. Serves 8.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add melted butter until crumbly.
Put crumbled mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are done.

title: mama's apple fritters(mrs. ada brooks)
directions: Sift together flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt. In medium bowl, with rotary beater, beat eggs, milk and vanilla until well combined.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Stir in apples.
In an electric skillet or heavy saucepan, slowly heat oil (1 1/2 to 2-inches deep).
Drop fritters by rounded tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
As they rise to surface, turn over with slotted utensil.
Fry until golden brown on both sides (4 to 5 minutes in all).
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot, sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Makes about 12 fritters.

title: cool whip dessert
directions: Mix first three ingredients, add beaten eggs; mix well.
Add chopped pecans.
Spread real thin on large cookie sheet that is well-greased and floured.
Be sure it is a large cookie sheet or two small ones or it will run over.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.
Crumble, add 1 large carton Cool Whip or 2 small ones; mix well.

title: hardeville cheese meat loaf
directions: If the venison comes from north country, you will need to wash well or soak in vinegar.
If it comes from the south, you roast as you would beef.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Whip cream and add to softened cream cheese.
Combine with sugar and vanilla.
Pour this mixture into 2 baked pie crusts. Spread 1 can of blueberry pie filling over the top.
One can covers 2 (8-inch) pies.
Chill for several hours.

title: sweet and sour shrimp
directions: In large, heavy skillet, combine reserved pineapple juice, water, lemon juice, sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce and ginger.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and clear.
Add shrimp; cook 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except rice; heat through. Serve with rice.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cherry cheese coffeecake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, egg yolk, powdered sugar, salt and vanilla.
In a large circle, place crescents with the points toward the center and slightly overlapping.
Crimp the outside edge to keep the filling in.
Place cream cheese mixture in a circle in the middle of crescents.
Put pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Pull inside of crescents to the outside. Bake 22 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Drizzle with powdered sugar frosting.
(I warm about 1/2 cup ready to spread frosting in the microwave and drizzle over cake.)

title: orange rice salad
directions: Place the cheese, pineapple and juice, sugar and gelatin in a pan. Simmer until gelatin is dissolved. Add the baby food. Stir, then cool until consistency of gravy. Add the rice and the whipped topping. Chill until firm.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift and measure dry ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well in dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and berries.
Stir and mix well.
Add nuts.
Do not overstir.
Pour in 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans, greased and dusted.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press 1/2 of mixture into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes only. Cool.

title: pizza dough
directions: Combine flour, yeast, salt and sugar in mixing bowl and stir. Add oil and water.
Mix together.
Knead by hand for 3 minutes. Shape and put in bowl.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down; divide into 2 equal pieces.
Shape into round balls or leave in 1 piece for 16-inch pizza.
Let dough rest for 4 minutes.
Roll out.

title: zucchini roast
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 18.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and flour in a large mixing bowl.
Add crushed pineapple, melted butter and broken up bread pieces.
Mix well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
This is a simple but delicious potato substitute.

title: chicken apple salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: hearty tortellini soup
directions: Saute garlic in butter for 2 minutes.
Add tortellini and broth and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add thawed spinach and tomatoes.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: holiday wreath cookies
directions: Melt oleo in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows melt and mixture is syrupy.
Remove from heat and add food coloring.
Add corn flakes.
Stir until well coated.
Using 1/2 cup mixture and buttered finger, shape into wreath on wax paper.
Dot with cinnamon candies.
Let cool.
Makes 16 wreaths.

title: tuna salad crescent-wiches
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Combine tuna, pickles, salad dressing, celery and water chestnuts. Separate crescent dough into 8 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal. Spoon about 1/2 cup tuna mixture on one end of rectangle. Fold dough in half over filling. Press edges with a fork to seal. Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 18 minutes or until light and golden brown. Remove from oven and top each with cheese slice. Sprinkle with paprika. Return to oven 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese softens. Serve immediately. Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: donna moon's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the sugar, flour and salt.
Mix together and heat until boiling the oleo, cocoa and water.
Pour the chocolate mixture over the flour and sugar and mix together. Add the eggs, buttermilk mixture, vanilla and cinnamon (optional).
Pour into greased sheet pan.
Bake 18 minutes at 400°.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; simmer until thick.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with top crust.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: ice coffee
directions: Pour coffee in a glass.
Add milk and sugar.
Add ice.
Make ice cold.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; drain sauce from shrimp.
Blend sauce with cream cheese.
Cut up shrimp.
Mix into cream cheese mixture.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Sift flour, spices and combine with oil and sugar.
Add one egg at a time; add water, nuts, vanilla.
Add sweet potatoes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Oil large skillet or pan.
Pour in 1/2 of corn meal mixture.
Sprinkle hamburger, onions, peppers and cheese on top and then pour remainder of corn meal on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes until brown and done in middle.

title: bran muffins
directions: Toss dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs and buttermilk and mix well.
Fold in Bran Flakes.
Bake desired amount of muffins in greased muffin tins at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Batter can be stored in refrigerator for 4 to 6 weeks.
Muffins can be frozen.

title: easy marshmallow chocolate pie
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk in top of double boiler.
Let cool.
Fold in whipped cream and Baker's chocolate.
Pour into a cooked pie crust.
Refrigerate and serve with Cool Whip and sprinkle grated chocolate on top.
Can make a day ahead.

title: morivan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 8 ingredients in a saucepan; mix well.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Combine water and soda; mix well.
Add to cooled brown sugar mixture.
Set aside.
Sift flour and baking powder together; gradually add to brown sugar mixture. Mix well until blended.
Spoon into greased 9-inch square pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.

title: spaghetti with broccoli
directions: Microwave broccoli on high for 3 minutes in covered dish with 1/4 cup of water.
Drain.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add garlic and cook for 30 seconds.
Add broccoli and red pepper flakes.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth, cooked spaghetti and cheese.
Toss on low heat for 1 minute.
Salt to taste.
Serve with grated cheese to sprinkle over top.
Serves 4-6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo, water and peanuts.
Cook on medium heat until peanuts have popped and about stopped popping.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir quickly, then pour into greased pan. Shake out and do not try to spread with spoon.
When cool empty on waxed paper and break into pieces.

title: tuna noodle
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Slowly stir in milk.
Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Add cheese a handful at a time.
In casserole dish, layer 1/2 noodles, mushrooms and tuna. Put 1/2 cheese mixture over, then layer noodles and cheese mixture over top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
May wish to crumble potato chips on top.

title: lemon squares
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Spread over baked crust and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: cranberry-apple punch
directions: Heat 2 quarts water and the sugar to boiling, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over tea in heatproof container.
Cover; steep 3 to 5 minutes.
Cool.
Chill all ingredients.
Just before serving, stir together in large punch bowl.
Makes 60 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: fruit salad
directions: To juice of pineapple, oranges and lemon, add sugar, oleo, flour and eggs.
Cook until thick.
Cool and pour into 1/2 pint of whipping cream, whipped.
Pour over fruit.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix together all ingredients except apples until well mixed.
Stir in diced apples. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting:

title: glorena's cake
directions: Mix and bake
cake according to directions, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When
done,
while
hot, punch holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand
milk
and
coconut
creme on cake. Let cool. Ice with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Better second day.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper with seasoning packet (included with Ramen noodles).
Toss with dry ingredients (including noodles).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: double layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugars.
Beat in yolks, water and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together and stir into butter mixture.
Pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle evenly with chocolate chips.
Beat whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Beat in 1 cup of brown sugar gradually.
Spoon over cookie mixture in pan, spreading evenly into corners.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: fibre rich bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour and next 5 ingredients. Mix well.
In saucepan, heat water, brown sugar, egg and oleo until very warm.
Add to flour.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in remaining flour to make firm dough.
Knead 5 to 8 minutes on floured surface.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise until double.

title: strawberry cream
directions: Freeze banana halves until firm.
Combine all ingredients and blend until smooth.
Serve in tall glasses.
Yields 2 (8 ounce) glasses.

title: jello-ice cream dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O with 3 cups boiling water until dissolved. Add ice cream, a little at a time, until no more dissolves.
Chill.

title: pizza on rye
directions: Brown and drain meats.
Stir in other ingredients.
Put on rye bread by teaspoon and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix with spinach, mushrooms, hard-cooked eggs, bacon and croutons.

title: easy stew
directions: Brown meat in oil; drain.
Add onion soup mix, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and carrots;
simmer
hours.
Add
peas,
consomme
and celery. Simmer 40 minutes.
If needed, thicken with cornstarch.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Put filling in bottom of pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Sprinkle cake mix over filling. Sprinkle nuts over mixture. Cut butter into small pieces over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice dressing
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Add all other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in baking dish; bake at 350 degrees until rice is done.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Blend in the large egg. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt; add to mixture. Add the vanilla.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Chill 1 to 2 hours. Take one part out at a time.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon iced ambrosia bars
directions: Mix together; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine oranges, pineapple, coconut and marshmallows. In small bowl, combine yogurt, sugar substitute and coconut extract. Mix gently with fruit mixture. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Makes 8 2/3 cup servings. 128 calories per serving.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix with sugar and flour.
Melt butter. Pour over mixture. Crumble Ritz crackers over this. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over Cool Whip and stir.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar.
Add
one egg at a time.
Beat well after each	egg.
Sift
flour
with baking powder and add alternately with
milk.
Add
flavorings.
Butter tube pan and sprinkle lightly with
flour.
Bake
at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Do not open oven door while cooking.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each egg.
Add soda and flour and bananas alternating. Add nuts.
Grease loaf pan.

title: microwave chocolate and butterscotch fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with foil.
In small bowl, place butterscotch chips and 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk; set aside.
In medium bowl, place chocolate chips, remaining sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Microwave on High 1 minute; stir until chips are melted.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread into pan. Microwave butterscotch chips on High 45 seconds; stir until chips are melted.
Spread evenly over chocolate layer.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off foil and cut into squares.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Boil syrup and sugar until bubbly.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Stir and spread out in buttered pan.
Lay on bars, let melt and spread out.
Cut into bars while warm.
Chill.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Add sugar, vanilla, soda and water; beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, cinnamon and salt; beat well.
Fold in pears. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350°.
Very good!

title: tuna casserole
directions: Blend soup and	milk
in
1-quart
casserole.
Stir
in tuna, eggs and peas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add potato chips on top for 6 minutes.

title: shrimp sunomono(japanese-style salad)
directions: Rinse shrimp with cold water; pat dry with paper towels.
Set aside.
Combine vinegar, sesame oil, sugar, salt and monosodium glutamate; mix well.
Refrigerate dressing for at least 1 hour before serving to allow flavors to blend.
Combine shrimp, cucumber, celery and green onion.
Pour dressing over shrimp and vegetable mixture just before serving; toss.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes.
Place in cold water to keep from turning brown after peeled.
Slice into disks thickness of silver dollar.
Boil in water for 30 minutes or until they begin to fall apart.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: veg-casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into your casserole.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Boil raisins and soda in water for 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.
Cream both sugars, shortening and eggs.
Add molasses, flour, salt and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Add raisins.
Spray small pans with Pam and fill half full with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 5 cans.

title: grilled corn-on-the-cob
directions: Cream together butter and salt until fluffy.
Add herbs and blend into butter.
Keep butter at room temperature for 1 hour to mellow.
Turn back husks of corn; remove silks.
Place each ear on a piece of heavy foil.
Spread corn with about 1 tablespoon of the butter.
Lay husks back in position.
Wrap corn securely. Grill ears directly on hot coals, turning frequently, for 12 to 15 minutes or until corn is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dig deep salad
directions: Place each ingredient in order given into single layer in clear bowl.
Spread the mayonnaise over peas and seal to edge. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the mayonnaise.
Seal with plastic wrap and refrigerate a couple of hours or overnight.
About 1 hour before serving, garnish with 3 or 4 hard-boiled eggs, sliced very thin.
Sprinkle with paprika and cover with plastic wrap, again, until served.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: korambiethes(greek butter cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar together well.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and baking powder.
Slowly add flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Dough should be just right, barely sticking to your hands.
Take a small amount and roll into a ball.
Pat down and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes. Bottom should be light brown.
After they have cooled a bit, dust with confectioners sugar.
Recipe makes approximately 50 cookies.

title: scoma's cioppino
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Add garlic and saute until garlic is browned.
Add onion, wine, bay leaves and oregano.
Cook 10 minutes over low heat.
Add crushed tomatoes and sugar.
Season to taste with salt.
Simmer 20 minutes, adding more wine if it evaporates too quickly.
Add crab, clams, prawns, shrimp and crab meat.
Cook until clams open, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: butter bean pie
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Brown ground chuck, onions and bell pepper and drain.
Mix salsa and tomato paste together.

title: sugar-free banana ice cream
directions: In a large bowl or electric mixer, combine milk, bananas, pecans, vanilla and sweetener.
When well mixed, add dry topping mix and dry pudding mix.
Mix well and pour into freezer can or 1/2 gallon ice cream freezer.
Add enough 2% milk to come up to fill line and freeze by freezer directions.
Makes 1/2 gallon.
Chill can before pouring ingredients into can.
Chill beaters before mixing ingredients.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss together; top with grated cheese (Velveeta or American) and crushed potato chips.
Cook until bubbly at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: apricot sweet potatoes
directions: Drain apricots, reserving syrup.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and orange rind; blend well.
Gradually add apricot syrup, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over medium flame for two minutes.
Add apricots and butter.
Stir until butter is melted.

title: german slaw
directions: Bring to a boil the vinegar, oil and sugar.
Pour over shredded or chopped slaw.
Mix together.

title: baked chicken delite
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken.
Roll in flour.
Place in deep baking dish and cover.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: kosher dill
directions: Wash cucumbers well and let stand overnight in cold water. Pack in jars and add to each jar, the first 6 ingredients. Combine apple vinegar, salt and water.
Boil and pour over cucumbers.
Seal.

title: christmas bishop bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Leave nuts, cherries and dates whole.
Bake in loaf pan at 250° to 300° for 1 hour or until done.
There is no shortening.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Heat the applesauce and Jell-O and dissolve. Add the pineapple. Cool and add 7-Up.

title: carrot cake(fourteen karat)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Add and mix well the cooking oil and 4 eggs.
Stir in the walnuts, pineapple and carrots.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: gumbo or okra soup
directions: Fry a slice of bacon; drain off and fry several slices of onions until brown.
Add tomatoes, okra and chopped parsley and cook in 3 pints of broth (any kind) for 3 hours.
Salt and pepper. In chicken broth the same quantity of okra, used for thickening instead of tomatoes, forms chicken gumbo soup.

title: easy pigs
directions: Brown beef with onion, then add rice to tomato soup and tomato sauce.
Mix well and add to beef.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over raw cabbage in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix well to cover cabbage.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Stir together and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with 1/2 can onions and brown in the oven.
Put cheese on top.

title: diabetic banana cream pie
directions: In a bowl, whisk milk and pudding mix for 2 minutes or until slightly thickened. Add sour cream; mix well. Fold 1 1/2 cups whipped topping into mixture. Place 1/2 of the banana slices in the crust. Top with 1/2 of the pudding mixture. Repeat layers. Spread with the remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours before serving. Keep pie refrigerated.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Beat egg until light.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Cream together with shortening and melted chocolate.
Blend well.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix milk into flour mixture and combine with shortening mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except for oleo and crackers.
Pour in casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted oleo over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: barbie cups
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off excess grease.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and garlic powder.
Add Tabasco sauce to your taste; mix well.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Place tuna into mixing bowl.
Blend soup and water; add to tuna.
