Add frozen peas (unthawed), 1 cup noodles and green onion. Toss to mix lightly.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining noodles.
Cover and refrigerate, if desired, for baking later or place into 375° oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with cashews, if desired.
(You may substitute canned chunk style chicken for the tuna to make Chopstick Chicken.)

title: maple oatmeal pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup and butter in mixer 2 to 3 minutes; add oatmeal and milk.
Beat 1 minute.
Add maple flavoring.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 375° for 20 minutes.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: In a blender, blend well first 3 ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Top with shredded cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: old fashion pumpkin fruit cake
directions: Cream the shortening with sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat well, then beat in molasses, buttermilk and pumpkin.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and spices.
Mix with dates, fruit, raisins and nuts.
Stir into batter, mixing well. Turn into greased large tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool cake.
A simple orange icing brings out additional flavor.

title: orange punch
directions: Microwave oranges and lemons until warm.
Squeeze.
Pour juice from oranges and lemons and sugar into a gallon jug.
Fill with water and mix well.
Chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, soup, Cheddar cheese and sour cream in a large bowl; mix well.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 12.

title: perdue oven stuffer(roaster in microwave)
directions: Rub inside and outside of roaster with minimum amount of salt. Put breast side down in covered microwave container with 1 1/2 cups water.
Microwave on High for 20 minutes.
Turn breast side up and cook on bake (60%) for 10 minutes.
Check pop up indicator.
Do in 10 minute increments until pop up shows.
Once indicator is up, cook 5 more minutes on bake to insure doneness at bone.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute or "sweat" onions and garlic in the oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes. Adjust seasoning.
Salt may be added at this time but is not necessary.
Serve over chips and top with cheese, if desired.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Combine water, vinegar and dressing mix in a jar; cover tightly and shake well.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly until coated.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: praline coconut cake
directions: Bake our toasted coconut cake mix in oblong pan as directed. Finish with Praline Topping (following).
Makes 16 servings.

title: mother's blueberry cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Cream oleo/butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add alternately milk and dry ingredients to the butter and sugar mixture.
Stir in blueberries.
Bake in a 10 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: danielle's irish soda bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Combine butter and buttermilk.
Combine dry ingredients, caraway seed and raisins.
Pour in egg mixture; mix very well.
Pour into well-greased bread pan.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done, at 350°.

title: yams and pineapple
directions: Open and drain the can of yams.
Put yams in a casserole dish. Open can of crushed pineapple and add to the yams with the juice. Mash the yams and pineapple a couple of times.
Place approximately 12 large marshmallows on top of the yams.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
If very brown, remove early.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and heat through.
Serves 6.

title: pinto bean tacos
directions: Heat taco shells according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, combine pinto beans, tomato sauce, chili peppers, chili powder, oregano and cumin.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Mash beans slightly, if desired.
Spoon bean mixture into taco shells.
Pass lettuce, tomato and cheese for toppings.
Serve with salsa, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: *Note:
Measure oatmeal and blend in a blender to a fine powder.

title: jimmy cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and coffee.
Stir in dry ingredients, then jimmies and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in 2 or 3 round layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with a fudge frosting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine meat, cracker crumbs, egg, onion and salt.
Form into small meatballs. Brown in oil. Combine rice and pepper.
Place rice in 2-quart casserole dish. Place cooked meatballs on top of rice.
Combine cheese spread, broccoli, tomatoes and basil. Pour over rice and meatballs. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: kolaches
directions: Combine milk, sugar and shortening in saucepan; heat until milk is scalded.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast into warm water; stir to dissolve.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, egg, potatoes and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour; mix well.
Dough should be sticky to make softer kolaches.
Cover; let rise in a warm place, free from draft, for about 45 minutes or until double in bulk.
Punch down; divide dough in half.
Pinch off small bits of dough about the size of a walnut; place on greased cookie sheet or flat pan.
Let rise until double in bulk. Punch down in center with thumb or index finger; spoon fillings into indentions.
Sprinkle topping over filling.
Bake in preheated 375-400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown. Remove from oven and brush with butter to soften crust.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add salt, lemon juice and water.
Add one egg with 1 cup of flour until used.
Cream well.
Add baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Top with sliced fresh strawberries and kiwi fruit.

title: layered tuna salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, green onions and mustard; set aside. Toss tuna with dill.
In a 3-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, shells, cucumber, tomato, tuna, peas and bacon.
Spread salad dressing mixture over bacon, sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Toss to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add flour one cup at a time.
Add extract and grape juice with soda in it; stir well.
Fold in fruit and nuts that have been dredged in flour; beat well.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in well.
Bake in tube pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake for 4 hours at 250°.
It make take a little longer than 4 hours.

title: chicken taco salad
directions: Stir-fry chicken in oil for 4 to 5 minutes or until tender. Reduce heat.
Stir in salsa.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir together salad dressing, avocado and hot pepper sauce.

title: boston cream cheese pie
directions: Make cake mix as directed.
Put in greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine the cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in sour cream. Pour evenly over top of cake.
Return to oven at 350° for another 35 minutes.
Loosen from side; cool.
Melt chocolate squares and butter.
Add in remaining
ingredients.
Take cake out of pan; frost with chocolate mixture.

title: cauliflower soup(blomkalsuppe)
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter and add carrots and parsley. Cook slowly 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle flour over mixture and stir well.
Add 2 cups heated stock.
Stir to a smooth sauce.
Add remainder of stock and boil until carrots are well done.
Add cauliflower pieces, cut finely.
Stir in cream and salt.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together; sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Serve with chips.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of pan or baking dish.
Mix chicken broth and soup and beat until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix melted margarine, salt, pepper, flour and milk to make batter. Pour on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: saturday night sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef; chop and drain. Add soup, catsup and mustard. Reheat.

title: hawaiian chicken bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine chicken, pineapple and mayonnaise and mix lightly.
Separate dough into four rectangles. Place about one-fourth of the chicken mixture in the center of each rectangle.
Stretch corners of dough over filling; twist ends and seal edges.
Brush with melted margarine or butter and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Make 8 sandwiches.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve.

title: angel cheese cake pie
directions: Combine flour, nuts and brown sugar.
Cut in butter to make a crumb mixture.
Place in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Cool.
Remove 1/4 cup of mixture.
Press remaining mixture into pie pan.

title: stuffed summer squash
directions: Cook squash in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain and cool enough to cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp and seeds to make 4 shells.
Mash pulp and seeds in mixing bowl.
Melt margarine in small skillet; add bread crumbs and fry until lightly browned on medium heat.
To pulp and seeds, add browned crumbs, spinach, cheese and seasonings and mix well.
Pile into squash shells.
Broil 3 inches from medium heat for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatine
in
cold
water.
Beat egg yolks and mix well
with	brown
sugar,
milk and pumpkin.
Add salt and spices. Place
over
double
boiler and cook until thickened. Remove from heat and add gelatine.
Cool and in meantime, beat egg whites to form
soft peaks.
Add sugar a little at a time and beat
until forms
stiff peaks.
Fold into cooled pumpkin mixture.
Spoon into
baked
pie
shell
and top with whipped cream.
Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend half of dried beef with remaining ingredients; shape into 2 balls.
Refrigerate 1 hour to harden, then roll in remaining beef.
For one ball, cut recipe in half.

title: black-eyed peas casserole
directions: Combine everything together.
Put in casserole dish and lay bacon
over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: twelve beans of christmas soup
directions: Boil beans in water and lemon juice for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Bring to second boil and simmer with ham shank until beans are tender, about 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and continue cooking another hour.
Remove meat from bone, return to soup and enjoy a hearty meal.
Serve with corn bread or your favorite crusty French bread.

title: molded asparagus salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, water and salt. Bring to a boil and dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat. Add gelatin and onion to boiled mixture. Cool. Combine remaining ingredients and add to liquid. Pour mixture in large greased mold or individual molds. Chill. Serves 6 to 8.

title: salmon devils
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks.
Put all ingredients into a food processor except pimento and parsley. Using steel blade mix well.
Divide mixture among egg whites, heaping high. Garnish and serve.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Drain pineapple and add water to juice to make 3/4 cup.
Add to Jell-O.
Fold in carrots, pineapple (and nuts, if desired).
Chill until firm. Unmold.
Garnish with additional pineapple and carrot curls, if desired.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut up steak into cubes; brown steak, chopped celery, onions, salt and pepper to taste.
Add water, soy sauce, sugar and molasses.
Bring to boil; add cornstarch to thicken.
Serve over rice.

title: french strawberry torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch round layer pan. Mix biscuit mix and sugar.
Add shortening, egg and 1/4 cup milk. Beat one minute at medium speed on electric mixer or vigorously by hand.
Add vanilla.
Beat 1/2 minute longer.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Allow to cool in pan 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool.

title: chili con carne
directions: Sprinkle large skillet with salt; add ground meat and onions. Cook until onions are tender and meat is browned.
Add garlic powder, sugar, catsup, chili beans and crushed tomatoes.
Let simmer for 30 minutes or so; serve.

title: kim's guacamole
directions: Add all ingredients into bowl and mix with fork until chunky. Top with shredded Longhorn cheese.

title: baked buttercup squash (microwave)
directions: Wash and cut squash in quarters, remove seeds and place in 8-inch square pyrex dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
In hollow of squash quarters add 1 Tbsp. brown sugar and dot of oleo. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on high for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: papa's feather cake(century old recipe)
directions: Cream butter thoroughly; add sugar slowly, beating constantly. Add baking powder sifted with flour.
Alternate milk and flour in mixing.
Add egg whites, beaten stiff, to be folded in last.
Add vanilla.

title: mom's rice pudding
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and condensed milk together; add to cooked rice.
Put on stove, bring to a low boil, remove after 1/2 to 1 minute.
Add vanilla and raisins, cinnamon or nutmeg.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, baking soda and egg.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Beat down, cover, let rise until light. Stir down; turn into 2-quart greased casserole.
Cover; let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: my favorite party mix
directions: Bring sauce to a boil.
Pour over rest of ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well!
Bake in cake pans or cookie sheets for 1 hour at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put cherries and pineapple in a pan and mix them together. Pour dry cake mix all over top of fruit.
Slice butter on top. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour or until top is brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain fat.
Mix in Ro-Tel, soup and seasoning mix.
Simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour with cocoa, baking powder and salt; set aside. Lightly grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat at medium speed, butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
With mixer at low speed, beat in flour mixture in 4 additions alternately with milk in 3 additions, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add grated chocolate and vanilla. Bake for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes, then turn from pan.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, pineapple juice, lemon juice and salt. Cook until thick over low heat, stirring constantly.
(You may add cornstarch, if necessary.)
Cool.
Important to cool.
Add celery, pineapple, apples and nuts.
Gently fold in whipped cream. Spoon into 8-inch square pan and freeze.
To serve, cut into squares and garnish with cherries.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut shortening or lard into dry ingredients.
Stir in buttermilk slowly.
Mix lightly.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter or mold with hands.

title: mary's cheese enchiladas
directions: Spread sour cream on tortillas.
Sprinkle on top of sour cream the cheese, onions, olives and peppers.
Roll tortillas.

title: broccoli mushroom quiche
directions: Heat oil in 10 inch fry pan; saute onions, thyme, basil, broccoli over medium heat.
After 5 minutes, add mushrooms and salt.
Saute until tender.
Remove from heat and drain juices.
In a bowl, beat eggs and add sour cream, cheeses, salt, pepper.
Put vegetable mixture in pie shell and pour cheese mixture over it. Bake 40-45 minutes until golden and puffy.
Let sit 10 minutes before cutting.

title: bountiful salad
directions: In a large
bowl,
toss
all ingredients with dressing. Cover and store in
refrigerator for 3 days.
Toss ingredients about twice a day.
Before serving, sprinkle evenly with salt.

title: rice krispies dessert
directions: Combine.
Press 1/2 mixture into bottom of 9 X 13 cake pan. Cover with 1/2 gallon of softened vanilla ice cream.
Sprinkle remaining cereal mixture on top.
Freeze until firm.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave cheese and picante sauce in a 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High for 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted, stirring well.
Serve hot with chips or raw vegetables. Makes 3 cups.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes and onions into very thin slices. Grease a 14 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place a layer of potatoes, a layer of onions and a layer of grated cheese in the dish.
(Use about 1/2 of each of these ingredients.) Sprinkle lightly with flour, salt and pepper.
Repeat the layering, ending with cheese. Again, sprinkle lightly with flour, salt and pepper.
Cut each bacon slice into 5 or 6 pieces.
Place the bacon pieces on top. Nearly cover with milk.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
The potatoes may be turned with a spoon while cooking to insure even baking and avoid overbrowning of bacon.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in coconut, milk and pecans.
Add crushed vanilla wafers.
Cook in a tube or loaf pan for 1 1/4 hours at 300°.
Cool completely.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and 1 stick margarine with electric mixer.
Pour into a casserole and heat in a 350° oven until thoroughly heated.
Combine the other stick of margarine with corn flakes and nuts.
Pour over potato mixture and return to oven for a few minutes until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup, milk and 1 cup of cheese together.
Place 1/3 of the sour cream mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread it evenly, then place 1 tablespoon of the remaining sour cream mixture on a tortilla pad at one end.
Add 1/6 of the chicken and vegetables; roll up.
After all pads are full and rolled, put them in the pan.
Use the remaining sour cream mixture and cheese to cover them.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix and sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: soft cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well.
Dry and pierce several times with fork. Bake at 400° for about 1 hour, or until soft.
Cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; carefully scoop potato pulp into bowl (leave 1/2 of pulp to keep the potato skin intact).
Set skins aside.
To the pulp, add yogurt, salt, pepper, paprika and 1/2 cheese; mix until light and fluffy.
Stuff potato skins with mixture.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Top with remaining cheese and crumbled bacon.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: a good casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Saute pepper, onion and celery in butter.
Add to browned sausage.
Combine soup mix in boiling water in a large saucepan; stir in rice, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Combine sausage mix and rice mix.
Add salt.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes until hot. Serves 10.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a 3-quart pot, bring milk to a boil.
Add rice.
Stir well. Lower heat and bring to boil again.
Let simmer 35 minutes.

title: crab and corn bisque
directions: Saute celery, green onions and green pepper in butter in a Dutch oven.
Add soup, corn, half and half, milk, bay leaves, thyme, garlic, pepper and hot sauce.
Cook until heated.
Gently stir in crabmeat and heat.
Discard bay leaves.
Garnish with parsley and lemon slices.
Yield: 11 cups.

title: meatballs 'n gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into meatballs and brown.
Put in crock-pot with 2 cans Franco-American beef gravy.
Cook 2 hours on high.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in salted water until tender, then drain and mash.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Add to eggplant; place in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle liberally with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Take thin slices of Butternip cheese.
This cheese is bought at gourmet shop.
Arrange on platter with a side dish of apple butter to spread on cheese slices.

title: pineapple corn bread
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Sift again and add corn meal; mix thoroughly.
Combine egg, milk, crushed pineapple and shortening.
Pour into flour mixture and stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Do not beat.
Turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: plantation molasses pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl, stirring slowly to prevent air bubbles.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in bottom half of oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 30 to 35 minutes, or until silver knife comes from center clean.

title: strawberry float punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar, cold water, extracts and juices.
Cool until serving time.
Add ginger ale and frozen strawberries.
Add ice cubes or crushed ice.

title: chicken n' orange sauce
directions: Brown chicken in margarine.
Remove chicken from pan.
Mix flour, brown sugar and ginger.
Stir until smooth; add orange juice and water.
Stir until thick.
Add chicken.
Cover and cook 1/2 hour.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add flour,
milk and cheese.
After this makes a sauce, add carrots.
Spoon into a casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs or grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated thoroughly.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Place first four ingredients in order in crock-pot (all raw). Mix the remaining ingredients and pour on top.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix together well in large mixing bowl:
walnuts or pecans, cake mix, pudding, oil, rum and eggs.
Pour mixture into a Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let cool for 1 minute, then flip onto plate.
When cooled for 10 minutes, pour glaze over cake.

title: spicy chocolate crackle top cookies(low-fat - 1 gram)
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat softened margarine, brown sugar, yogurt, egg whites and vanilla with electric mixer until blended.
The mix will look curdled.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops.
Pour off fat.
Mix soup, water and pepper.
Pour over chops.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and cinnamon and let stand. Mix brown sugar, flour, oatmeal, margarine and nuts until crumbly. Pour over rhubarb in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Cook clams in saucepan in butter, garlic and parsley.
Stir in soup, milk, clam liquid and cheese.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Serve over pasta.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour and salt; stir in next three ingredients.
Stir and bring to a boil; cook two minutes.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks; return to hot mixture.
Cook and stir two minutes.
Cool and pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites with vanilla and cream of tartar to soft peak.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff; spread on pie.
Bake 12 minutes or until brown.

title: tofu "cheese cake" pie
directions: Blend condensed milk, lemon juice and tofu in electric blender until firm and smooth.
Pour into crust.
Top with fruit pie filling or other drained canned or fresh fruit.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: Saute the onions until soft; add the cabbage.
Season with sugar, salt and pepper.
Add more oil, if necessary, and soy sauce until the cabbage and onions are brown.
Add the noodles.
Tastes best with boldly seasoned foods.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Layer broccoli, tuna and mushrooms in a small casserole dish. Combine buttermilk, onion flakes, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon french toast(light)
directions: In a shallow bowl, using a wire whisk or a fork, beat the egg and egg whites until foamy.
Add the milk, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat well; set aside.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: rocky road squares
directions: In a 3	quart
casserole
dish combine chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and
peanut
butter.
Microwave	at
Medium (50°)
for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until chips are softened, stirring
after
half the time.
Stir until smooth and melted. Mix in marshmallows and peanuts.
Spread in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: chicken dish
directions: Line pan with chicken.
Pour soup mixed with sour cream over chicken.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Melt butter and pour over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in bowl and pour into Pam sprayed Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Fry the meat.
Stir in the cheese until it melts.
Take off heat, then add 1 can soup and mayonnaise.
Cool.
Spread on hamburger bun (open-face).
Put under broiler to heat through and serve.

title: laclede gas company teriyaki
directions: Thread meat on a wooden skewers (8) and place in a shallow pan.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over skewered meat. Let stand 2 hours.
Lift out skewers.
Arrange on a broiler rack. Broil about 3 inches from heat, turning to brown on all sides, about 10 to 15 minutes or until desired doneness.
(Good cooked outdoors over charcoal also.)

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: the port's pork sherry
directions: Mix ingredients and put in plastic bag with pork roast. Refrigerate 24 hours, turning bag, and roast every 2 to 3 hours as convenient.
Remove roast from bag and cook in oven for 2 3/4 to 3 hours at 325°.
Baste frequently with mixture from plastic bag.

title: baked alaska
directions: Mix the egg yolks, water and cake mix and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Freeze.
Put the ice cream over the first layer 1/2-inch from pan edges.
Freeze.
Beat the egg whites and cream of tartar. Add the sugar gradually, one tablespoon at a time.
Beat until stiff, then add to other layers and seal edges.
Brown meringue. Freeze again.
Eat that day.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: meatball appetizers
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, deviled ham, bread crumbs, salt, dry mustard and hot pepper sauce.
Shape into meatballs about 3/4-inch round. Arrange in shallow pan and bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: scallops and rice au gratin
directions: Coarsely chop scallops.
In butter cook green pepper, onion and celery until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add scallops. Place one-half the rice into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with one-half the scallop mixture and one-half the shredded cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: onion crusted chicken
directions: Place chicken between plastic and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using metal mallet or rolling pin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine margarine, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Stir well.
Dredge chicken in butter mixture, then crushed onion rings.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and top with remaining onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked elbow macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, pepper and salt, if desired.
Add milk gradually and cheese; continue to cook until cheese is melted.
Cook macaroni as directed on side of box.
Combine sauce with drained macaroni and pour into a greased casserole.
Top with buttered
bread crumbs and bake in moderately hot oven for about 20 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour with soda.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to butter-sugar mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.

title: roasted garlic potatoes
directions: Spray large cookie sheet with cooking spray.
In small bowl, combine corn oil, garlic and rosemary.
Arrange potato slices on cookie sheet.
Brush with corn oil mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and pepper.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until lightly browned and crisp.

title: dried fruit bake
directions: Pour in baking dish; bake until syrup is thick, about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, butter and the milk, into which has been stirred the soda and salt.
Add flavoring.
Pour in about 3 pints of flour and knead until it is firm.
Roll thin and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: fruit and cookie dip
directions: Mix well and chill until ready to serve. Serve with fruit and cookies for dipping. Ginger snaps and vanilla wafers are great.

title: green pea salad
directions: Layer lettuce in casserole.
Combine celery, onion, green pepper and peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Layer all ingredients.
Top layer is cheese and bacon last.
Yield: Serves 15 or 20.

title: chocolate french mint pie
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Melt chocolate; add to mixture and beat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and peppermint.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill for 24 hours.
Before serving, whip cream until stiff; add remaining vanilla.
Use as topping on pie. Top with chocolate shavings.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix all together.
Spoon fruit over mixture trying to cover the entire area.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 minutes until firm at 325°.

title: salmon soup
directions: In a 5 qt. pot, melt 1/4 c. butter on low heat.
Add the celery and saute briefly.
Add the salmon and its juice, flaking with a fork, and stir.
Drain potatoes and dice; add to soup.
Add remaining butter and flour to thicken.
Add condensed milk and stir.
Add enough room temperature milk to reach desired thickness and amount of soup you want, and stir.
Add dash of salt and any additional seasonings, such as celery salt or pepper, to taste. Stir slowly over medium heat until warm.
Never boil!

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In large pan cook pepper and onion in oleo
3 to 4 minutes. Remove from heat and add all other ingredients.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, alternate tortillas, soup mixture and cheese twice.
Heat in 325° oven till bubbling.

title: teriyaki glazed chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°, line baking dish with foil.
In sauce pan combine glaze ingredients.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, boil 1 minute or until sugar dissolves. Brush over chicken, bake 20 minutes, turn and brush with glaze, bake 25-35 minutes more.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread but do not let rise.
Break one loaf into pieces on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt butter and add brown sugar, cinnamon, pudding and milk.
Mix together and pour over bread pieces in pan.
Break second loaf of bread.
Place on top of the first.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert pan while hot onto platter.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all ingredients except nuts in large bowl.
Microwave at Medium (50%) until chocolate bits are melted, 3 to 5 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased square baking dish, 8 x 8-inches.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve the package of jello in the 2 cups of boiling water. Add the cherry pie filling.
Stir and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt over hot water the cream cheese, marshmallows and then beat in the package of Dream Whip.
Spread over the set jello.
